8 //
9 // This provides C++ code generation targeting the Itanium C++ ABI. The class
10 // in this file generates structures that follow the Itanium C++ ABI, which is
11 // documented at:
12 // https://itanium-cxx-abi.github.io/cxx-abi/abi.html
13 // https://itanium-cxx-abi.github.io/cxx-abi/abi-eh.html
14 //
15 // It also supports the closely-related ARM ABI, documented at:
16 // https://developer.arm.com/documentation/ihi0041/g/
17 //
18 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

73  RecordArgABI getRecordArgABI(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const override {
74  // If C++ prohibits us from making a copy, pass by address.
75  if (!RD->canPassInRegisters())
76  return RAA_Indirect;
77  return RAA_Default;
78  }
79 
80  bool isThisCompleteObject(GlobalDecl GD) const override {
81  // The Itanium ABI has separate complete-object vs. base-object
82  // variants of both constructors and destructors.
83  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
84  switch (GD.getDtorType()) {
85  case Dtor_Complete:
86  case Dtor_Deleting:
87  return true;
88 
89  case Dtor_Base:
90  return false;
91 
92  case Dtor_Comdat:
93  llvm_unreachable("emitting dtor comdat as function?");
94  }
95  llvm_unreachable("bad dtor kind");
96  }
97  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
98  switch (GD.getCtorType()) {
99  case Ctor_Complete:
100  return true;
101 
102  case Ctor_Base:
103  return false;
104 
105  case Ctor_CopyingClosure:
106  case Ctor_DefaultClosure:
107  llvm_unreachable("closure ctors in Itanium ABI?");
108 
109  case Ctor_Comdat:
110  llvm_unreachable("emitting ctor comdat as function?");
111  }
112  llvm_unreachable("bad dtor kind");
113  }
114 
115  // No other kinds.
116  return false;
117  }

188  bool shouldDynamicCastCallBeNullChecked(bool SrcIsPtr,

191  /// Determine whether we know that all instances of type RecordTy will have
192  /// the same vtable pointer values, that is distinct from all other vtable
193  /// pointers. While this is required by the Itanium ABI, it doesn't happen in
194  /// practice in some cases due to language extensions.
195  bool hasUniqueVTablePointer(QualType RecordTy) {
196  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = RecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
197 
198  // Under -fapple-kext, multiple definitions of the same vtable may be
199  // emitted.
200  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().AssumeUniqueVTables ||
201  getContext().getLangOpts().AppleKext)
202  return false;
203 
204  // If the type_info* would be null, the vtable might be merged with that of
205  // another type.
206  if (!CGM.shouldEmitRTTI())
207  return false;
208 
209  // If there's only one definition of the vtable in the program, it has a
210  // unique address.
211  if (!llvm::GlobalValue::isWeakForLinker(CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD)))
212  return true;
213 
214  // Even if there are multiple definitions of the vtable, they are required
215  // by the ABI to use the same symbol name, so should be merged at load
216  // time. However, if the class has hidden visibility, there can be
217  // different versions of the class in different modules, and the ABI
218  // library might treat them as being the same.
219  if (CGM.GetLLVMVisibility(RD->getVisibility()) !=
220  llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility)
221  return false;
222 
223  return true;
224  }
225 
226  bool shouldEmitExactDynamicCast(QualType DestRecordTy) override {
227  return hasUniqueVTablePointer(DestRecordTy);
228  }

389  /**************************** RTTI Uniqueness ******************************/
390 
391 protected:
392  /// Returns true if the ABI requires RTTI type_info objects to be unique
393  /// across a program.
394  virtual bool shouldRTTIBeUnique() const { return true; }
395 
396 public:
397  /// What sort of unique-RTTI behavior should we use?
398  enum RTTIUniquenessKind {
399  /// We are guaranteeing, or need to guarantee, that the RTTI string
400  /// is unique.
401  RUK_Unique,
402 
403  /// We are not guaranteeing uniqueness for the RTTI string, so we
404  /// can demote to hidden visibility but must use string comparisons.
405  RUK_NonUniqueHidden,
406 
407  /// We are not guaranteeing uniqueness for the RTTI string, so we
408  /// have to use string comparisons, but we also have to emit it with
409  /// non-hidden visibility.
410  RUK_NonUniqueVisible
411  };
412 
413  /// Return the required visibility status for the given type and linkage in
414  /// the current ABI.
415  RTTIUniquenessKind
416  classifyRTTIUniqueness(QualType CanTy,
417  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage) const;
418  friend class ItaniumRTTIBuilder;
419 
420  void emitCXXStructor(GlobalDecl GD) override;
421 
422  std::pair<llvm::Value *, const CXXRecordDecl *>
423  LoadVTablePtr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address This,
424  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) override;
425 
426  private:
427  bool hasAnyUnusedVirtualInlineFunction(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
428  const auto &VtableLayout =
429  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
430 
431  for (const auto &VtableComponent : VtableLayout.vtable_components()) {
432  // Skip empty slot.
433  if (!VtableComponent.isUsedFunctionPointerKind())
434  continue;
435 
436  const CXXMethodDecl *Method = VtableComponent.getFunctionDecl();
437  if (!Method->getCanonicalDecl()->isInlined())
438  continue;
439 
440  StringRef Name = CGM.getMangledName(VtableComponent.getGlobalDecl());
441  auto *Entry = CGM.GetGlobalValue(Name);
442  // This checks if virtual inline function has already been emitted.
443  // Note that it is possible that this inline function would be emitted
444  // after trying to emit vtable speculatively. Because of this we do
445  // an extra pass after emitting all deferred vtables to find and emit
446  // these vtables opportunistically.
447  if (!Entry || Entry->isDeclaration())
448  return true;
449  }
450  return false;
451  }
452 
453  bool isVTableHidden(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
454  const auto &VtableLayout =
455  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
456 
457  for (const auto &VtableComponent : VtableLayout.vtable_components()) {
458  if (VtableComponent.isRTTIKind()) {
459  const CXXRecordDecl *RTTIDecl = VtableComponent.getRTTIDecl();
460  if (RTTIDecl->getVisibility() == Visibility::HiddenVisibility)
461  return true;
462  } else if (VtableComponent.isUsedFunctionPointerKind()) {
463  const CXXMethodDecl *Method = VtableComponent.getFunctionDecl();
464  if (Method->getVisibility() == Visibility::HiddenVisibility &&
465  !Method->isDefined())
466  return true;
467  }
468  }
469  return false;
470  }
471 };

544 
545 CodeGen::CGCXXABI *CodeGen::CreateItaniumCXXABI(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
546  switch (CGM.getContext().getCXXABIKind()) {
547  // For IR-generation purposes, there's no significant difference
548  // between the ARM and iOS ABIs.
549  case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
550  case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
551  case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
552  return new ARMCXXABI(CGM);
553 
554  case TargetCXXABI::AppleARM64:
555  return new AppleARM64CXXABI(CGM);
556 
557  case TargetCXXABI::Fuchsia:
558  return new FuchsiaCXXABI(CGM);
559 
560  // Note that AArch64 uses the generic ItaniumCXXABI class since it doesn't
561  // include the other 32-bit ARM oddities: constructor/destructor return values
562  // and array cookies.
563  case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
564  return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /*UseARMMethodPtrABI=*/true,
565  /*UseARMGuardVarABI=*/true);
566 
567  case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
568  return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /*UseARMMethodPtrABI=*/true);
569 
570  case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
571  return new WebAssemblyCXXABI(CGM);
572 
573  case TargetCXXABI::XL:
574  return new XLCXXABI(CGM);
575 
576  case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
577  if (CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch()
578  == llvm::Triple::le32) {
579  // For PNaCl, use ARM-style method pointers so that PNaCl code
580  // does not assume anything about the alignment of function
581  // pointers.
582  return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /*UseARMMethodPtrABI=*/true);
583  }
584  return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM);
585 
586  case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
587  llvm_unreachable("Microsoft ABI is not Itanium-based");
588  }
589  llvm_unreachable("bad ABI kind");
590 }
591 
592 llvm::Type *
593 ItaniumCXXABI::ConvertMemberPointerType(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
594  if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
595  return CGM.PtrDiffTy;
596  return llvm::StructType::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
597 }
598 
599 /// In the Itanium and ARM ABIs, method pointers have the form:
600 /// struct { ptrdiff_t ptr; ptrdiff_t adj; } memptr;
601 ///
602 /// In the Itanium ABI:
603 /// - method pointers are virtual if (memptr.ptr & 1) is nonzero
604 /// - the this-adjustment is (memptr.adj)
605 /// - the virtual offset is (memptr.ptr - 1)
606 ///
607 /// In the ARM ABI:
608 /// - method pointers are virtual if (memptr.adj & 1) is nonzero
609 /// - the this-adjustment is (memptr.adj >> 1)
610 /// - the virtual offset is (memptr.ptr)
611 /// ARM uses 'adj' for the virtual flag because Thumb functions
612 /// may be only single-byte aligned.
613 ///
614 /// If the member is virtual, the adjusted 'this' pointer points
615 /// to a vtable pointer from which the virtual offset is applied.
616 ///
617 /// If the member is non-virtual, memptr.ptr is the address of
618 /// the function to call.
619 CGCallee ItaniumCXXABI::EmitLoadOfMemberFunctionPointer(
620  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, Address ThisAddr,
621  llvm::Value *&ThisPtrForCall,
622  llvm::Value *MemFnPtr, const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
623  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
624 
625  const FunctionProtoType *FPT =
626  MPT->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
627  auto *RD =
628  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(MPT->getClass()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
629 
630  llvm::Constant *ptrdiff_1 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 1);
631 
632  llvm::BasicBlock *FnVirtual = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.virtual");
633  llvm::BasicBlock *FnNonVirtual = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.nonvirtual");
634  llvm::BasicBlock *FnEnd = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.end");
635 
636  // Extract memptr.adj, which is in the second field.
637  llvm::Value *RawAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemFnPtr, 1, "memptr.adj");
638 
639  // Compute the true adjustment.
640  llvm::Value *Adj = RawAdj;
641  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI)
642  Adj = Builder.CreateAShr(Adj, ptrdiff_1, "memptr.adj.shifted");
643 
644  // Apply the adjustment and cast back to the original struct type
645  // for consistency.
646  llvm::Value *This = ThisAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
647  This = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Builder.getInt8Ty(), This, Adj);
648  ThisPtrForCall = This;
649 
650  // Load the function pointer.
651  llvm::Value *FnAsInt = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemFnPtr, 0, "memptr.ptr");
652 
653  // If the LSB in the function pointer is 1, the function pointer points to
654  // a virtual function.
655  llvm::Value *IsVirtual;
656  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI)
657  IsVirtual = Builder.CreateAnd(RawAdj, ptrdiff_1);
658  else
659  IsVirtual = Builder.CreateAnd(FnAsInt, ptrdiff_1);
660  IsVirtual = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(IsVirtual, "memptr.isvirtual");
661  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsVirtual, FnVirtual, FnNonVirtual);
662 
663  // In the virtual path, the adjustment left 'This' pointing to the
664  // vtable of the correct base subobject. The "function pointer" is an
665  // offset within the vtable (+1 for the virtual flag on non-ARM).
666  CGF.EmitBlock(FnVirtual);
667 
668  // Cast the adjusted this to a pointer to vtable pointer and load.
669  llvm::Type *VTableTy = CGF.CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy;
670  CharUnits VTablePtrAlign =
671  CGF.CGM.getDynamicOffsetAlignment(ThisAddr.getAlignment(), RD,
672  CGF.getPointerAlign());
673  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(
674  Address(This, ThisAddr.getElementType(), VTablePtrAlign), VTableTy, RD);
675 
676  // Apply the offset.
677  // On ARM64, to reserve extra space in virtual member function pointers,
678  // we only pay attention to the low 32 bits of the offset.
679  llvm::Value *VTableOffset = FnAsInt;
680  if (!UseARMMethodPtrABI)
681  VTableOffset = Builder.CreateSub(VTableOffset, ptrdiff_1);
682  if (Use32BitVTableOffsetABI) {
683  VTableOffset = Builder.CreateTrunc(VTableOffset, CGF.Int32Ty);
684  VTableOffset = Builder.CreateZExt(VTableOffset, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
685  }
686 
687  // Check the address of the function pointer if CFI on member function
688  // pointers is enabled.
689  llvm::Constant *CheckSourceLocation;
690  llvm::Constant *CheckTypeDesc;
691  bool ShouldEmitCFICheck = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall) &&
692  CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD);
693  bool ShouldEmitVFEInfo = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().VirtualFunctionElimination &&
694  CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD);
695  bool ShouldEmitWPDInfo =
696  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables &&
697  // Don't insert type tests if we are forcing public visibility.
698  !CGM.AlwaysHasLTOVisibilityPublic(RD);
699  llvm::Value *VirtualFn = nullptr;
700 
701  {
702  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
703  llvm::Value *TypeId = nullptr;
704  llvm::Value *CheckResult = nullptr;
705 
706  if (ShouldEmitCFICheck || ShouldEmitVFEInfo || ShouldEmitWPDInfo) {
707  // If doing CFI, VFE or WPD, we will need the metadata node to check
708  // against.
709  llvm::Metadata *MD =
710  CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForVirtualMemPtrType(QualType(MPT, 0));
711  TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), MD);
712  }
713 
714  if (ShouldEmitVFEInfo) {
715  llvm::Value *VFPAddr =
716  Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, VTable, VTableOffset);
717 
718  // If doing VFE, load from the vtable with a type.checked.load intrinsic
719  // call. Note that we use the GEP to calculate the address to load from
720  // and pass 0 as the offset to the intrinsic. This is because every
721  // vtable slot of the correct type is marked with matching metadata, and
722  // we know that the load must be from one of these slots.
723  llvm::Value *CheckedLoad = Builder.CreateCall(
724  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_checked_load),
725  {VFPAddr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 0), TypeId});
726  CheckResult = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CheckedLoad, 1);
727  VirtualFn = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CheckedLoad, 0);
728  } else {
729  // When not doing VFE, emit a normal load, as it allows more
730  // optimisations than type.checked.load.
731  if (ShouldEmitCFICheck || ShouldEmitWPDInfo) {
732  llvm::Value *VFPAddr =
733  Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, VTable, VTableOffset);
734  llvm::Intrinsic::ID IID = CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD)
735  ? llvm::Intrinsic::type_test
736  : llvm::Intrinsic::public_type_test;
737 
738  CheckResult =
739  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IID), {VFPAddr, TypeId});
740  }
741 
742  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
743  VirtualFn = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(
744  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::load_relative,
745  {VTableOffset->getType()}),
746  {VTable, VTableOffset});
747  } else {
748  llvm::Value *VFPAddr =
749  CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, VTable, VTableOffset);
750  VirtualFn = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
751  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()), VFPAddr,
752  CGF.getPointerAlign(), "memptr.virtualfn");
753  }
754  }
755  assert(VirtualFn && "Virtual fuction pointer not created!");
756  assert((!ShouldEmitCFICheck || !ShouldEmitVFEInfo || !ShouldEmitWPDInfo ||
757  CheckResult) &&
758  "Check result required but not created!");
759 
760  if (ShouldEmitCFICheck) {
761  // If doing CFI, emit the check.
762  CheckSourceLocation = CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc());
763  CheckTypeDesc = CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(MPT, 0));
764  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
765  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_VMFCall),
766  CheckSourceLocation,
767  CheckTypeDesc,
768  };
769 
770  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall)) {
771  CGF.EmitTrapCheck(CheckResult, SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail);
772  } else {
773  llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
774  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
775  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
776  llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateCall(
777  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {VTable, AllVtables});
778  CGF.EmitCheck(std::make_pair(CheckResult, SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall),
779  SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
780  {VTable, ValidVtable});
781  }
782 
783  FnVirtual = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
784  }
785  } // End of sanitizer scope
786 
787  CGF.EmitBranch(FnEnd);
788 
789  // In the non-virtual path, the function pointer is actually a
790  // function pointer.
791  CGF.EmitBlock(FnNonVirtual);
792  llvm::Value *NonVirtualFn = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(
793  FnAsInt, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()),
794  "memptr.nonvirtualfn");
795 
796  // Check the function pointer if CFI on member function pointers is enabled.
797  if (ShouldEmitCFICheck) {
798  CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getClass()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
799  if (RD->hasDefinition()) {
800  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
801 
802  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
803  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_NVMFCall),
804  CheckSourceLocation,
805  CheckTypeDesc,
806  };
807 
808  llvm::Value *Bit = Builder.getFalse();
809  for (const CXXRecordDecl *Base : CGM.getMostBaseClasses(RD)) {
810  llvm::Metadata *MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(
811  getContext().getMemberPointerType(
812  MPT->getPointeeType(),
813  getContext().getRecordType(Base).getTypePtr()));
814  llvm::Value *TypeId =
815  llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), MD);
816 
817  llvm::Value *TypeTest =
818  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
819  {NonVirtualFn, TypeId});
820  Bit = Builder.CreateOr(Bit, TypeTest);
821  }
822 
823  CGF.EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Bit, SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall),
824  SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
825  {NonVirtualFn, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.IntPtrTy)});
826 
827  FnNonVirtual = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
828  }
829  }
830 
831  // We're done.
832  CGF.EmitBlock(FnEnd);
833  llvm::PHINode *CalleePtr =
834  Builder.CreatePHI(llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()), 2);
835  CalleePtr->addIncoming(VirtualFn, FnVirtual);
836  CalleePtr->addIncoming(NonVirtualFn, FnNonVirtual);
837 
838  CGCallee Callee(FPT, CalleePtr);
839  return Callee;
840 }
841 
842 /// Compute an l-value by applying the given pointer-to-member to a
843 /// base object.
844 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberDataPointerAddress(
845  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, Address Base, llvm::Value *MemPtr,
846  const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
847  assert(MemPtr->getType() == CGM.PtrDiffTy);
848 
849  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
850 
851  // Apply the offset, which we assume is non-null.
852  return Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, Base.emitRawPointer(CGF), MemPtr,
853  "memptr.offset");
854 }
855 
856 /// Perform a bitcast, derived-to-base, or base-to-derived member pointer
857 /// conversion.
858 ///
859 /// Bitcast conversions are always a no-op under Itanium.
860 ///
861 /// Obligatory offset/adjustment diagram:
862 /// <-- offset --> <-- adjustment -->
863 /// |--------------------------|----------------------|--------------------|
864 /// ^Derived address point ^Base address point ^Member address point
865 ///
866 /// So when converting a base member pointer to a derived member pointer,
867 /// we add the offset to the adjustment because the address point has
868 /// decreased; and conversely, when converting a derived MP to a base MP
869 /// we subtract the offset from the adjustment because the address point
870 /// has increased.
871 ///
872 /// The standard forbids (at compile time) conversion to and from
873 /// virtual bases, which is why we don't have to consider them here.
874 ///
875 /// The standard forbids (at run time) casting a derived MP to a base
876 /// MP when the derived MP does not point to a member of the base.
877 /// This is why -1 is a reasonable choice for null data member
878 /// pointers.
879 llvm::Value *
880 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerConversion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
881  const CastExpr *E,
882  llvm::Value *src) {
883  assert(E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer ||
884  E->getCastKind() == CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer ||
885  E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer);
886 
887  // Under Itanium, reinterprets don't require any additional processing.
888  if (E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer) return src;
889 
890  // Use constant emission if we can.
891  if (isa<llvm::Constant>(src))
892  return EmitMemberPointerConversion(E, cast<llvm::Constant>(src));
893 
894  llvm::Constant *adj = getMemberPointerAdjustment(E);
895  if (!adj) return src;
896 
897  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
898  bool isDerivedToBase = (E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer);
899 
900  const MemberPointerType *destTy =
901  E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
902 
903  // For member data pointers, this is just a matter of adding the
904  // offset if the source is non-null.
905  if (destTy->isMemberDataPointer()) {
906  llvm::Value *dst;
907  if (isDerivedToBase)
908  dst = Builder.CreateNSWSub(src, adj, "adj");
909  else
910  dst = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(src, adj, "adj");
911 
912  // Null check.
913  llvm::Value *null = llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(src->getType());
914  llvm::Value *isNull = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(src, null, "memptr.isnull");
915  return Builder.CreateSelect(isNull, src, dst);
916  }
917 
918  // The this-adjustment is left-shifted by 1 on ARM.
919  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
920  uint64_t offset = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(adj)->getZExtValue();
921  offset <<= 1;
922  adj = llvm::ConstantInt::get(adj->getType(), offset);
923  }
924 
925  llvm::Value *srcAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(src, 1, "src.adj");
926  llvm::Value *dstAdj;
927  if (isDerivedToBase)
928  dstAdj = Builder.CreateNSWSub(srcAdj, adj, "adj");
929  else
930  dstAdj = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(srcAdj, adj, "adj");
931 
932  return Builder.CreateInsertValue(src, dstAdj, 1);
933 }
934 
935 llvm::Constant *
936 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerConversion(const CastExpr *E,
937  llvm::Constant *src) {
938  assert(E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer ||
939  E->getCastKind() == CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer ||
940  E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer);
941 
942  // Under Itanium, reinterprets don't require any additional processing.
943  if (E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer) return src;
944 
945  // If the adjustment is trivial, we don't need to do anything.
946  llvm::Constant *adj = getMemberPointerAdjustment(E);
947  if (!adj) return src;
948 
949  bool isDerivedToBase = (E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer);
950 
951  const MemberPointerType *destTy =
952  E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
953 
954  // For member data pointers, this is just a matter of adding the
955  // offset if the source is non-null.
956  if (destTy->isMemberDataPointer()) {
957  // null maps to null.
958  if (src->isAllOnesValue()) return src;
959 
960  if (isDerivedToBase)
961  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWSub(src, adj);
962  else
963  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWAdd(src, adj);
964  }
965 
966  // The this-adjustment is left-shifted by 1 on ARM.
967  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
968  uint64_t offset = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(adj)->getZExtValue();
969  offset <<= 1;
970  adj = llvm::ConstantInt::get(adj->getType(), offset);
971  }
972 
973  llvm::Constant *srcAdj = src->getAggregateElement(1);
974  llvm::Constant *dstAdj;
975  if (isDerivedToBase)
976  dstAdj = llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWSub(srcAdj, adj);
977  else
978  dstAdj = llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWAdd(srcAdj, adj);
979 
980  llvm::Constant *res = ConstantFoldInsertValueInstruction(src, dstAdj, 1);
981  assert(res != nullptr && "Folding must succeed");
982  return res;
983 }
984 
985 llvm::Constant *
986 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitNullMemberPointer(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
987  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
988  // A NULL pointer is represented as -1.
989  if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
990  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, -1ULL, /*isSigned=*/true);
991 
992  llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 0);
993  llvm::Constant *Values[2] = { Zero, Zero };
994  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Values);
995 }
996 
997 llvm::Constant *
998 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberDataPointer(const MemberPointerType *MPT,
999  CharUnits offset) {
1000  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
1001  // A pointer to data member is an offset from the base address of
1002  // the class object containing it, represented as a ptrdiff_t
1003  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, offset.getQuantity());
1004 }
1005 
1006 llvm::Constant *
1007 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberFunctionPointer(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
1008  return BuildMemberPointer(MD, CharUnits::Zero());
1009 }
1010 
1011 llvm::Constant *ItaniumCXXABI::BuildMemberPointer(const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
1012  CharUnits ThisAdjustment) {
1013  assert(MD->isInstance() && "Member function must not be static!");
1014 
1015  CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
1016 
1017  // Get the function pointer (or index if this is a virtual function).
1018  llvm::Constant *MemPtr[2];
1019  if (MD->isVirtual()) {
1020  uint64_t Index = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(MD);
1021  uint64_t VTableOffset;
1022  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
1023  // Multiply by 4-byte relative offsets.
1024  VTableOffset = Index * 4;
1025  } else {
1026  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1027  CharUnits PointerWidth = Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
1028  Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default));
1029  VTableOffset = Index * PointerWidth.getQuantity();
1030  }
1031 
1032  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
1033  // ARM C++ ABI 3.2.1:
1034  // This ABI specifies that adj contains twice the this
1035  // adjustment, plus 1 if the member function is virtual. The
1036  // least significant bit of adj then makes exactly the same
1037  // discrimination as the least significant bit of ptr does for
1038  // Itanium.
1039  MemPtr[0] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, VTableOffset);
1040  MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
1041  2 * ThisAdjustment.getQuantity() + 1);
1042  } else {
1043  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
1044  // For a virtual function, [the pointer field] is 1 plus the
1045  // virtual table offset (in bytes) of the function,
1046  // represented as a ptrdiff_t.
1047  MemPtr[0] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, VTableOffset + 1);
1048  MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
1049  ThisAdjustment.getQuantity());
1050  }
1051  } else {
1052  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = MD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1053  llvm::Type *Ty;
1054  // Check whether the function has a computable LLVM signature.
1055  if (Types.isFuncTypeConvertible(FPT)) {
1056  // The function has a computable LLVM signature; use the correct type.
1057  Ty = Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(MD));
1058  } else {
1059  // Use an arbitrary non-function type to tell GetAddrOfFunction that the
1060  // function type is incomplete.
1061  Ty = CGM.PtrDiffTy;
1062  }
1063  llvm::Constant *addr = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(MD, Ty);
1064 
1065  MemPtr[0] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(addr, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
1066  MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
1067  (UseARMMethodPtrABI ? 2 : 1) *
1068  ThisAdjustment.getQuantity());
1069  }
1070 
1071  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(MemPtr);
1072 }
1073 
1074 llvm::Constant *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointer(const APValue &MP,
1075  QualType MPType) {
1076  const MemberPointerType *MPT = MPType->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
1077  const ValueDecl *MPD = MP.getMemberPointerDecl();
1078  if (!MPD)
1079  return EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
1080 
1081  CharUnits ThisAdjustment = getContext().getMemberPointerPathAdjustment(MP);
1082 
1083  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(MPD))
1084  return BuildMemberPointer(MD, ThisAdjustment);
1085 
1086  CharUnits FieldOffset =
1087  getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(getContext().getFieldOffset(MPD));
1088  return EmitMemberDataPointer(MPT, ThisAdjustment + FieldOffset);
1089 }
1090 
1091 /// The comparison algorithm is pretty easy: the member pointers are
1092 /// the same if they're either bitwise identical *or* both null.
1093 ///
1094 /// ARM is different here only because null-ness is more complicated.
1095 llvm::Value *
1096 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerComparison(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1097  llvm::Value *L,
1098  llvm::Value *R,
1099  const MemberPointerType *MPT,
1100  bool Inequality) {
1101  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1102 
1103  llvm::ICmpInst::Predicate Eq;
1104  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps And, Or;
1105  if (Inequality) {
1106  Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
1107  And = llvm::Instruction::Or;
1108  Or = llvm::Instruction::And;
1109  } else {
1110  Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
1111  And = llvm::Instruction::And;
1112  Or = llvm::Instruction::Or;
1113  }
1114 
1115  // Member data pointers are easy because there's a unique null
1116  // value, so it just comes down to bitwise equality.
1117  if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
1118  return Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, L, R);
1119 
1120  // For member function pointers, the tautologies are more complex.
1121  // The Itanium tautology is:
1122  // (L == R) <==> (L.ptr == R.ptr && (L.ptr == 0 || L.adj == R.adj))
1123  // The ARM tautology is:
1124  // (L == R) <==> (L.ptr == R.ptr &&
1125  // (L.adj == R.adj ||
1126  // (L.ptr == 0 && ((L.adj|R.adj) & 1) == 0)))
1127  // The inequality tautologies have exactly the same structure, except
1128  // applying De Morgan's laws.
1129 
1130  llvm::Value *LPtr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, 0, "lhs.memptr.ptr");
1131  llvm::Value *RPtr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, 0, "rhs.memptr.ptr");
1132 
1133  // This condition tests whether L.ptr == R.ptr. This must always be
1134  // true for equality to hold.
1135  llvm::Value *PtrEq = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LPtr, RPtr, "cmp.ptr");
1136 
1137  // This condition, together with the assumption that L.ptr == R.ptr,
1138  // tests whether the pointers are both null. ARM imposes an extra
1139  // condition.
1140  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LPtr->getType());
1141  llvm::Value *EqZero = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LPtr, Zero, "cmp.ptr.null");
1142 
1143  // This condition tests whether L.adj == R.adj. If this isn't
1144  // true, the pointers are unequal unless they're both null.
1145  llvm::Value *LAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, 1, "lhs.memptr.adj");
1146  llvm::Value *RAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, 1, "rhs.memptr.adj");
1147  llvm::Value *AdjEq = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LAdj, RAdj, "cmp.adj");
1148 
1149  // Null member function pointers on ARM clear the low bit of Adj,
1150  // so the zero condition has to check that neither low bit is set.
1151  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
1152  llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(LPtr->getType(), 1);
1153 
1154  // Compute (l.adj | r.adj) & 1 and test it against zero.
1155  llvm::Value *OrAdj = Builder.CreateOr(LAdj, RAdj, "or.adj");
1156  llvm::Value *OrAdjAnd1 = Builder.CreateAnd(OrAdj, One);
1157  llvm::Value *OrAdjAnd1EqZero = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, OrAdjAnd1, Zero,
1158  "cmp.or.adj");
1159  EqZero = Builder.CreateBinOp(And, EqZero, OrAdjAnd1EqZero);
1160  }
1161 
1162  // Tie together all our conditions.
1163  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(Or, EqZero, AdjEq);
1164  Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(And, PtrEq, Result,
1165  Inequality ? "memptr.ne" : "memptr.eq");
1166  return Result;
1167 }
1168 
1169 llvm::Value *
1170 ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1171  llvm::Value *MemPtr,
1172  const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
1173  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1174 
1175  /// For member data pointers, this is just a check against -1.
1176  if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer()) {
1177  assert(MemPtr->getType() == CGM.PtrDiffTy);
1178  llvm::Value *NegativeOne =
1179  llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(MemPtr->getType());
1180  return Builder.CreateICmpNE(MemPtr, NegativeOne, "memptr.tobool");
1181  }
1182 
1183  // In Itanium, a member function pointer is not null if 'ptr' is not null.
1184  llvm::Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, 0, "memptr.ptr");
1185 
1186  llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ptr->getType(), 0);
1187  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ptr, Zero, "memptr.tobool");
1188 
1189  // On ARM, a member function pointer is also non-null if the low bit of 'adj'
1190  // (the virtual bit) is set.
1191  if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
1192  llvm::Constant *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ptr->getType(), 1);
1193  llvm::Value *Adj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, 1, "memptr.adj");
1194  llvm::Value *VirtualBit = Builder.CreateAnd(Adj, One, "memptr.virtualbit");
1195  llvm::Value *IsVirtual = Builder.CreateICmpNE(VirtualBit, Zero,
1196  "memptr.isvirtual");
1197  Result = Builder.CreateOr(Result, IsVirtual);
1198  }
1199 
1200  return Result;
1201 }
1202 
1203 bool ItaniumCXXABI::classifyReturnType(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1204  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = FI.getReturnType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1205  if (!RD)
1206  return false;
1207 
1208  // If C++ prohibits us from making a copy, return by address.
1209  if (!RD->canPassInRegisters()) {
1210  auto Align = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(FI.getReturnType());
1211  FI.getReturnInfo() = ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(Align, /*ByVal=*/false);
1212  return true;
1213  }
1214  return false;
1215 }

1217 /// The Itanium ABI requires non-zero initialization only for data
1218 /// member pointers, for which '0' is a valid offset.
1219 bool ItaniumCXXABI::isZeroInitializable(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
1220  return MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer();
1221 }
1222 
1223 /// The Itanium ABI always places an offset to the complete object
1224 /// at entry -2 in the vtable.
1225 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitVirtualObjectDelete(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1226  const CXXDeleteExpr *DE,
1227  Address Ptr,
1228  QualType ElementType,
1229  const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor) {
1230  bool UseGlobalDelete = DE->isGlobalDelete();
1231  if (UseGlobalDelete) {
1232  // Derive the complete-object pointer, which is what we need
1233  // to pass to the deallocation function.
1234 
1235  // Grab the vtable pointer as an intptr_t*.
1236  auto *ClassDecl =
1237  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ElementType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1238  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(
1239  Ptr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()), ClassDecl);
1240 
1241  // Track back to entry -2 and pull out the offset there.
1242  llvm::Value *OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(
1243  CGF.IntPtrTy, VTable, -2, "complete-offset.ptr");
1244  llvm::Value *Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CGF.IntPtrTy, OffsetPtr,
1245  CGF.getPointerAlign());
1246 
1247  // Apply the offset.
1248  llvm::Value *CompletePtr = Ptr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
1249  CompletePtr =
1250  CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, CompletePtr, Offset);
1251 
1252  // If we're supposed to call the global delete, make sure we do so
1253  // even if the destructor throws.
1254  CGF.pushCallObjectDeleteCleanup(DE->getOperatorDelete(), CompletePtr,
1255  ElementType);
1256  }
1257 
1258  // FIXME: Provide a source location here even though there's no
1259  // CXXMemberCallExpr for dtor call.
1260  CXXDtorType DtorType = UseGlobalDelete ? Dtor_Complete : Dtor_Deleting;
1261  EmitVirtualDestructorCall(CGF, Dtor, DtorType, Ptr, DE);
1262 
1263  if (UseGlobalDelete)
1264  CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
1265 }
1266 
1267 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitRethrow(CodeGenFunction &CGF, bool isNoReturn) {
1268  // void __cxa_rethrow();
1269 
1270  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1271  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
1272 
1273  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_rethrow");
1274 
1275  if (isNoReturn)
1276  CGF.EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn, std::nullopt);
1277  else
1278  CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn);
1279 }

1281 static llvm::FunctionCallee getAllocateExceptionFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1282  // void *__cxa_allocate_exception(size_t thrown_size);
1283 
1284  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1285  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.SizeTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
1286 
1287  return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_allocate_exception");
1288 }
1289 
1290 static llvm::FunctionCallee getThrowFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1291  // void __cxa_throw(void *thrown_exception, std::type_info *tinfo,
1292  // void (*dest) (void *));
1293 
1294  llvm::Type *Args[3] = { CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy };
1295  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1296  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, Args, /*isVarArg=*/false);
1297 
1298  return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_throw");
1299 }
1300 
1301 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitThrow(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXThrowExpr *E) {
1302  QualType ThrowType = E->getSubExpr()->getType();
1303  // Now allocate the exception object.
1304  llvm::Type *SizeTy = CGF.ConvertType(getContext().getSizeType());
1305  uint64_t TypeSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ThrowType).getQuantity();
1306 
1307  llvm::FunctionCallee AllocExceptionFn = getAllocateExceptionFn(CGM);
1308  llvm::CallInst *ExceptionPtr = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(
1309  AllocExceptionFn, llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, TypeSize), "exception");
1310 
1311  CharUnits ExnAlign = CGF.getContext().getExnObjectAlignment();
1312  CGF.EmitAnyExprToExn(
1313  E->getSubExpr(), Address(ExceptionPtr, CGM.Int8Ty, ExnAlign));
1314 
1315  // Now throw the exception.
1316  llvm::Constant *TypeInfo = CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(ThrowType,
1317  /*ForEH=*/true);
1318 
1319  // The address of the destructor. If the exception type has a
1320  // trivial destructor (or isn't a record), we just pass null.
1321  llvm::Constant *Dtor = nullptr;
1322  if (const RecordType *RecordTy = ThrowType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1323  CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl());
1324  if (!Record->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
1325  CXXDestructorDecl *DtorD = Record->getDestructor();
1326  Dtor = CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(DtorD, Dtor_Complete));
1327  }
1328  }
1329  if (!Dtor) Dtor = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
1330 
1331  llvm::Value *args[] = { ExceptionPtr, TypeInfo, Dtor };
1332  CGF.EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(getThrowFn(CGM), args);
1333 }
1334 
1335 static llvm::FunctionCallee getItaniumDynamicCastFn(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1336  // void *__dynamic_cast(const void *sub,
1337  // global_as const abi::__class_type_info *src,
1338  // global_as const abi::__class_type_info *dst,
1339  // std::ptrdiff_t src2dst_offset);
1340 
1341  llvm::Type *Int8PtrTy = CGF.Int8PtrTy;
1342  llvm::Type *GlobInt8PtrTy = CGF.GlobalsInt8PtrTy;
1343  llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
1344  CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1345 
1346  llvm::Type *Args[4] = { Int8PtrTy, GlobInt8PtrTy, GlobInt8PtrTy, PtrDiffTy };
1347 
1348  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(Int8PtrTy, Args, false);
1349 
1350  // Mark the function as nounwind willreturn readonly.
1351  llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs(CGF.getLLVMContext());
1352  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1353  FuncAttrs.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::WillReturn);
1354  FuncAttrs.addMemoryAttr(llvm::MemoryEffects::readOnly());
1355  llvm::AttributeList Attrs = llvm::AttributeList::get(
1356  CGF.getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, FuncAttrs);
1357 
1358  return CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__dynamic_cast", Attrs);
1359 }
1360 
1361 static llvm::FunctionCallee getBadCastFn(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1362  // void __cxa_bad_cast();
1363  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, false);
1364  return CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_bad_cast");
1365 }
1366 
1367 /// Compute the src2dst_offset hint as described in the
1368 /// Itanium C++ ABI [2.9.7]
1369 static CharUnits computeOffsetHint(ASTContext &Context,
1370  const CXXRecordDecl *Src,
1371  const CXXRecordDecl *Dst) {
1372  CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1373  /*DetectVirtual=*/false);
1374 
1375  // If Dst is not derived from Src we can skip the whole computation below and
1376  // return that Src is not a public base of Dst. Record all inheritance paths.
1377  if (!Dst->isDerivedFrom(Src, Paths))
1378  return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-2ULL);
1379 
1380  unsigned NumPublicPaths = 0;
1381  CharUnits Offset;
1382 
1383  // Now walk all possible inheritance paths.
1384  for (const CXXBasePath &Path : Paths) {
1385  if (Path.Access != AS_public) // Ignore non-public inheritance.
1386  continue;
1387 
1388  ++NumPublicPaths;
1389 
1390  for (const CXXBasePathElement &PathElement : Path) {
1391  // If the path contains a virtual base class we can't give any hint.
1392  // -1: no hint.
1393  if (PathElement.Base->isVirtual())
1394  return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-1ULL);
1395 
1396  if (NumPublicPaths > 1) // Won't use offsets, skip computation.
1397  continue;
1398 
1399  // Accumulate the base class offsets.
1400  const ASTRecordLayout &L = Context.getASTRecordLayout(PathElement.Class);
1401  Offset += L.getBaseClassOffset(
1402  PathElement.Base->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
1403  }
1404  }
1405 
1406  // -2: Src is not a public base of Dst.
1407  if (NumPublicPaths == 0)
1408  return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-2ULL);
1409 
1410  // -3: Src is a multiple public base type but never a virtual base type.
1411  if (NumPublicPaths > 1)
1412  return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-3ULL);
1413 
1414  // Otherwise, the Src type is a unique public nonvirtual base type of Dst.
1415  // Return the offset of Src from the origin of Dst.
1416  return Offset;
1417 }

1419 static llvm::FunctionCallee getBadTypeidFn(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1420  // void __cxa_bad_typeid();
1421  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, false);
1422 
1423  return CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_bad_typeid");
1424 }

1431 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitBadTypeidCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1432  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = getBadTypeidFn(CGF);
1433  llvm::CallBase *Call = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn);
1434  Call->setDoesNotReturn();
1435  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();

1438 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitTypeid(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1439  QualType SrcRecordTy,
1440  Address ThisPtr,
1441  llvm::Type *StdTypeInfoPtrTy) {
1442  auto *ClassDecl =
1443  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SrcRecordTy->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1444  llvm::Value *Value = CGF.GetVTablePtr(ThisPtr, CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy,
1445  ClassDecl);
1446 
1447  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
1448  // Load the type info.
1449  Value = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(
1450  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::load_relative, {CGM.Int32Ty}),
1451  {Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, -4)});
1452  } else {
1453  // Load the type info.
1454  Value =
1455  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(StdTypeInfoPtrTy, Value, -1ULL);
1456  }
1457  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(StdTypeInfoPtrTy, Value,
1458  CGF.getPointerAlign());
1459 }

1465 
1466 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::emitDynamicCastCall(
1467  CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address ThisAddr, QualType SrcRecordTy,
1468  QualType DestTy, QualType DestRecordTy, llvm::BasicBlock *CastEnd) {
1469  llvm::Type *PtrDiffLTy =
1470  CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1471 
1472  llvm::Value *SrcRTTI =
1473  CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(SrcRecordTy.getUnqualifiedType());
1474  llvm::Value *DestRTTI =
1475  CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(DestRecordTy.getUnqualifiedType());
1476 
1477  // Compute the offset hint.
1478  const CXXRecordDecl *SrcDecl = SrcRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1479  const CXXRecordDecl *DestDecl = DestRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1480  llvm::Value *OffsetHint = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1481  PtrDiffLTy,
1482  computeOffsetHint(CGF.getContext(), SrcDecl, DestDecl).getQuantity());
1483 
1484  // Emit the call to __dynamic_cast.
1485  llvm::Value *Args[] = {ThisAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF), SrcRTTI, DestRTTI,
1486  OffsetHint};
1487  llvm::Value *Value =
1488  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getItaniumDynamicCastFn(CGF), Args);
1489 
1490  /// C++ [expr.dynamic.cast]p9:
1491  /// A failed cast to reference type throws std::bad_cast
1492  if (DestTy->isReferenceType()) {
1493  llvm::BasicBlock *BadCastBlock =
1494  CGF.createBasicBlock("dynamic_cast.bad_cast");
1495 
1496  llvm::Value *IsNull = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(Value);
1497  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNull, BadCastBlock, CastEnd);
1498 
1499  CGF.EmitBlock(BadCastBlock);
1500  EmitBadCastCall(CGF);
1501  }
1502 
1503  return Value;
1504 }
1505 
1506 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::emitExactDynamicCast(
1507  CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address ThisAddr, QualType SrcRecordTy,
1508  QualType DestTy, QualType DestRecordTy, llvm::BasicBlock *CastSuccess,
1509  llvm::BasicBlock *CastFail) {
1510  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1511 
1512  // Find all the inheritance paths.
1513  const CXXRecordDecl *SrcDecl = SrcRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1514  const CXXRecordDecl *DestDecl = DestRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1515  CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1516  /*DetectVirtual=*/false);
1517  (void)DestDecl->isDerivedFrom(SrcDecl, Paths);
1518 
1519  // Find an offset within `DestDecl` where a `SrcDecl` instance and its vptr
1520  // might appear.
1521  std::optional<CharUnits> Offset;
1522  for (const CXXBasePath &Path : Paths) {
1523  // dynamic_cast only finds public inheritance paths.
1524  if (Path.Access != AS_public)
1525  continue;
1526 
1527  CharUnits PathOffset;
1528  for (const CXXBasePathElement &PathElement : Path) {
1529  // Find the offset along this inheritance step.
1530  const CXXRecordDecl *Base =
1531  PathElement.Base->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1532  if (PathElement.Base->isVirtual()) {
1533  // For a virtual base class, we know that the derived class is exactly
1534  // DestDecl, so we can use the vbase offset from its layout.
1535  const ASTRecordLayout &L = Context.getASTRecordLayout(DestDecl);
1536  PathOffset = L.getVBaseClassOffset(Base);
1537  } else {
1538  const ASTRecordLayout &L =
1539  Context.getASTRecordLayout(PathElement.Class);
1540  PathOffset += L.getBaseClassOffset(Base);
1541  }
1542  }
1543 
1544  if (!Offset)
1545  Offset = PathOffset;
1546  else if (Offset != PathOffset) {
1547  // Base appears in at least two different places. Find the most-derived
1548  // object and see if it's a DestDecl. Note that the most-derived object
1549  // must be at least as aligned as this base class subobject, and must
1550  // have a vptr at offset 0.
1551  ThisAddr = Address(emitDynamicCastToVoid(CGF, ThisAddr, SrcRecordTy),
1552  CGF.VoidPtrTy, ThisAddr.getAlignment());
1553  SrcDecl = DestDecl;
1554  Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
1555  break;
1556  }
1557  }
1558 
1559  if (!Offset) {
1560  // If there are no public inheritance paths, the cast always fails.
1561  CGF.EmitBranch(CastFail);
1562  return llvm::PoisonValue::get(CGF.VoidPtrTy);
1563  }
1564 
1565  // Compare the vptr against the expected vptr for the destination type at
1566  // this offset. Note that we do not know what type ThisAddr points to in
1567  // the case where the derived class multiply inherits from the base class
1568  // so we can't use GetVTablePtr, so we load the vptr directly instead.
1569  llvm::Instruction *VPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
1570  ThisAddr.withElementType(CGF.VoidPtrPtrTy), "vtable");
1571  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(
1572  VPtr, CGM.getTBAAVTablePtrAccessInfo(CGF.VoidPtrPtrTy));
1573  llvm::Value *Success = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
1574  VPtr, getVTableAddressPoint(BaseSubobject(SrcDecl, *Offset), DestDecl));
1575  llvm::Value *Result = ThisAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
1576  if (!Offset->isZero())
1577  Result = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
1578  CGF.CharTy, Result,
1579  {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.PtrDiffTy, -Offset->getQuantity())});
1580  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Success, CastSuccess, CastFail);
1581  return Result;
1582 }
1583 
1584 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::emitDynamicCastToVoid(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1585  Address ThisAddr,
1586  QualType SrcRecordTy) {
1587  auto *ClassDecl =
1588  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SrcRecordTy->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1589  llvm::Value *OffsetToTop;
1590  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
1591  // Get the vtable pointer.
1592  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(
1593  ThisAddr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()),
1594  ClassDecl);
1595 
1596  // Get the offset-to-top from the vtable.
1597  OffsetToTop =
1598  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(CGM.Int32Ty, VTable, -2U);
1599  OffsetToTop = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
1600  CGM.Int32Ty, OffsetToTop, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), "offset.to.top");
1601  } else {
1602  llvm::Type *PtrDiffLTy =
1603  CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1604 
1605  // Get the vtable pointer.
1606  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(
1607  ThisAddr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()),
1608  ClassDecl);
1609 
1610  // Get the offset-to-top from the vtable.
1611  OffsetToTop =
1612  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(PtrDiffLTy, VTable, -2ULL);
1613  OffsetToTop = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
1614  PtrDiffLTy, OffsetToTop, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "offset.to.top");
1615  }
1616  // Finally, add the offset to the pointer.
1617  return CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, ThisAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF),
1618  OffsetToTop);
1619 }
1620 
1621 bool ItaniumCXXABI::EmitBadCastCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1622  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = getBadCastFn(CGF);
1623  llvm::CallBase *Call = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn);
1624  Call->setDoesNotReturn();
1625  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
1626  return true;
1627 }
1628 
1629 llvm::Value *
1630 ItaniumCXXABI::GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1631  Address This,
1632  const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
1633  const CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl) {
1634  llvm::Value *VTablePtr = CGF.GetVTablePtr(This, CGM.Int8PtrTy, ClassDecl);
1635  CharUnits VBaseOffsetOffset =
1636  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(ClassDecl,
1637  BaseClassDecl);
1638  llvm::Value *VBaseOffsetPtr =
1639  CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_64(
1640  CGF.Int8Ty, VTablePtr, VBaseOffsetOffset.getQuantity(),
1641  "vbase.offset.ptr");
1642 
1643  llvm::Value *VBaseOffset;
1644  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
1645  VBaseOffset = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
1646  CGF.Int32Ty, VBaseOffsetPtr, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4),
1647  "vbase.offset");
1648  } else {
1649  VBaseOffset = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
1650  CGM.PtrDiffTy, VBaseOffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "vbase.offset");
1651  }
1652  return VBaseOffset;
1653 }
1654 
1655 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitCXXConstructors(const CXXConstructorDecl *D) {
1656  // Just make sure we're in sync with TargetCXXABI.
1657  assert(CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants());
1658 
1659  // The constructor used for constructing this as a base class;
1660  // ignores virtual bases.
1661  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Base));
1662 
1663  // The constructor used for constructing this as a complete class;
1664  // constructs the virtual bases, then calls the base constructor.
1665  if (!D->getParent()->isAbstract()) {
1666  // We don't need to emit the complete ctor if the class is abstract.
1667  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Complete));
1668  }
1669 }
1670 
1671 CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgCounts
1672 ItaniumCXXABI::buildStructorSignature(GlobalDecl GD,
1673  SmallVectorImpl<CanQualType> &ArgTys) {
1674  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1675 
1676  // All parameters are already in place except VTT, which goes after 'this'.
1677  // These are Clang types, so we don't need to worry about sret yet.
1678 
1679  // Check if we need to add a VTT parameter (which has type global void **).
1680  if ((isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl()) ? GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Base
1681  : GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base) &&
1682  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl())->getParent()->getNumVBases() != 0) {
1683  LangAS AS = CGM.GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(nullptr);
1684  QualType Q = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(Context.VoidPtrTy, AS);
1685  ArgTys.insert(ArgTys.begin() + 1,
1686  Context.getPointerType(CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(Q)));
1687  return AddedStructorArgCounts::prefix(1);
1688  }
1689  return AddedStructorArgCounts{};
1690 }
1691 
1692 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitCXXDestructors(const CXXDestructorDecl *D) {
1693  // The destructor used for destructing this as a base class; ignores
1694  // virtual bases.
1695  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Base));
1696 
1697  // The destructor used for destructing this as a most-derived class;
1698  // call the base destructor and then destructs any virtual bases.
1699  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Complete));
1700 
1701  // The destructor in a virtual table is always a 'deleting'
1702  // destructor, which calls the complete destructor and then uses the
1703  // appropriate operator delete.
1704  if (D->isVirtual())
1705  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Deleting));
1706 }
1707 
1708 void ItaniumCXXABI::addImplicitStructorParams(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1709  QualType &ResTy,
1710  FunctionArgList &Params) {
1711  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl());
1712  assert(isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD));
1713 
1714  // Check if we need a VTT parameter as well.
1715  if (NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD)) {
1716  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1717 
1718  // FIXME: avoid the fake decl
1719  LangAS AS = CGM.GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(nullptr);
1720  QualType Q = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(Context.VoidPtrTy, AS);
1721  QualType T = Context.getPointerType(Q);
1722  auto *VTTDecl = ImplicitParamDecl::Create(
1723  Context, /*DC=*/nullptr, MD->getLocation(), &Context.Idents.get("vtt"),
1724  T, ImplicitParamKind::CXXVTT);
1725  Params.insert(Params.begin() + 1, VTTDecl);
1726  getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) = VTTDecl;
1727  }
1728 }
1729 
1730 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitInstanceFunctionProlog(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1731  // Naked functions have no prolog.
1732  if (CGF.CurFuncDecl && CGF.CurFuncDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
1733  return;
1734 
1735  /// Initialize the 'this' slot. In the Itanium C++ ABI, no prologue
1736  /// adjustments are required, because they are all handled by thunks.
1737  setCXXABIThisValue(CGF, loadIncomingCXXThis(CGF));
1738 
1739  /// Initialize the 'vtt' slot if needed.
1740  if (getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)) {
1741  getStructorImplicitParamValue(CGF) = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
1742  CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)), "vtt");
1743  }
1744 
1745  /// If this is a function that the ABI specifies returns 'this', initialize
1746  /// the return slot to 'this' at the start of the function.
1747  ///
1748  /// Unlike the setting of return types, this is done within the ABI
1749  /// implementation instead of by clients of CGCXXABI because:
1750  /// 1) getThisValue is currently protected
1751  /// 2) in theory, an ABI could implement 'this' returns some other way;
1752  /// HasThisReturn only specifies a contract, not the implementation
1753  if (HasThisReturn(CGF.CurGD))
1754  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(getThisValue(CGF), CGF.ReturnValue);
1755 }
1756 
1757 CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgs ItaniumCXXABI::getImplicitConstructorArgs(
1758  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXConstructorDecl *D, CXXCtorType Type,
1759  bool ForVirtualBase, bool Delegating) {
1760  if (!NeedsVTTParameter(GlobalDecl(D, Type)))
1761  return AddedStructorArgs{};
1762 
1763  // Insert the implicit 'vtt' argument as the second argument. Make sure to
1764  // correctly reflect its address space, which can differ from generic on
1765  // some targets.
1766  llvm::Value *VTT =
1767  CGF.GetVTTParameter(GlobalDecl(D, Type), ForVirtualBase, Delegating);
1768  LangAS AS = CGM.GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(nullptr);
1769  QualType Q = getContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(getContext().VoidPtrTy, AS);
1770  QualType VTTTy = getContext().getPointerType(Q);
1771  return AddedStructorArgs::prefix({{VTT, VTTTy}});
1772 }
1773 
1774 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::getCXXDestructorImplicitParam(
1775  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXDestructorDecl *DD, CXXDtorType Type,
1776  bool ForVirtualBase, bool Delegating) {
1777  GlobalDecl GD(DD, Type);
1778  return CGF.GetVTTParameter(GD, ForVirtualBase, Delegating);
1779 }
1780 
1781 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitDestructorCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1782  const CXXDestructorDecl *DD,
1783  CXXDtorType Type, bool ForVirtualBase,
1784  bool Delegating, Address This,
1785  QualType ThisTy) {
1786  GlobalDecl GD(DD, Type);
1787  llvm::Value *VTT =
1788  getCXXDestructorImplicitParam(CGF, DD, Type, ForVirtualBase, Delegating);
1789  QualType VTTTy = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1790 
1791  CGCallee Callee;
1792  if (getContext().getLangOpts().AppleKext &&
1793  Type != Dtor_Base && DD->isVirtual())
1794  Callee = CGF.BuildAppleKextVirtualDestructorCall(DD, Type, DD->getParent());
1795  else
1796  Callee = CGCallee::forDirect(CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GD), GD);
1797 
1798  CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, CGF.getAsNaturalPointerTo(This, ThisTy),
1799  ThisTy, VTT, VTTTy, nullptr);
1800 }
1801 
1802 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitVTableDefinitions(CodeGenVTables &CGVT,
1803  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1804  llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable = getAddrOfVTable(RD, CharUnits());
1805  if (VTable->hasInitializer())
1806  return;
1807 
1808  ItaniumVTableContext &VTContext = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext();
1809  const VTableLayout &VTLayout = VTContext.getVTableLayout(RD);
1810  llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
1811  llvm::Constant *RTTI =
1812  CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(CGM.getContext().getTagDeclType(RD));
1813 
1814  // Create and set the initializer.
1815  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
1816  auto components = builder.beginStruct();
1817  CGVT.createVTableInitializer(components, VTLayout, RTTI,
1818  llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage));
1819  components.finishAndSetAsInitializer(VTable);
1820 
1821  // Set the correct linkage.
1822  VTable->setLinkage(Linkage);
1823 
1824  if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && VTable->isWeakForLinker())
1825  VTable->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(VTable->getName()));
1826 
1827  // Set the right visibility.
1828  CGM.setGVProperties(VTable, RD);
1829 
1830  // If this is the magic class __cxxabiv1::__fundamental_type_info,
1831  // we will emit the typeinfo for the fundamental types. This is the
1832  // same behaviour as GCC.
1833  const DeclContext *DC = RD->getDeclContext();
1834  if (RD->getIdentifier() &&
1835  RD->getIdentifier()->isStr("__fundamental_type_info") &&
1836  isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getIdentifier() &&
1837  cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getIdentifier()->isStr("__cxxabiv1") &&
1838  DC->getParent()->isTranslationUnit())
1839  EmitFundamentalRTTIDescriptors(RD);
1840 
1841  // Always emit type metadata on non-available_externally definitions, and on
1842  // available_externally definitions if we are performing whole program
1843  // devirtualization. For WPD we need the type metadata on all vtable
1844  // definitions to ensure we associate derived classes with base classes
1845  // defined in headers but with a strong definition only in a shared library.
1846  if (!VTable->isDeclarationForLinker() ||
1847  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables) {
1848  CGM.EmitVTableTypeMetadata(RD, VTable, VTLayout);
1849  // For available_externally definitions, add the vtable to
1850  // @llvm.compiler.used so that it isn't deleted before whole program
1851  // analysis.
1852  if (VTable->isDeclarationForLinker()) {
1853  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables);
1854  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(VTable);
1855  }
1856  }
1857 
1858  if (VTContext.isRelativeLayout()) {
1859  CGVT.RemoveHwasanMetadata(VTable);
1860  if (!VTable->isDSOLocal())
1861  CGVT.GenerateRelativeVTableAlias(VTable, VTable->getName());
1862  }
1863 }
1864 
1865 bool ItaniumCXXABI::isVirtualOffsetNeededForVTableField(
1866  CodeGenFunction &CGF, CodeGenFunction::VPtr Vptr) {
1867  if (Vptr.NearestVBase == nullptr)
1868  return false;
1869  return NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD);
1870 }
1871 
1872 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPointInStructor(
1873  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass, BaseSubobject Base,
1874  const CXXRecordDecl *NearestVBase) {
1875 
1876  if ((Base.getBase()->getNumVBases() || NearestVBase != nullptr) &&
1877  NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD)) {
1878  return getVTableAddressPointInStructorWithVTT(CGF, VTableClass, Base,
1879  NearestVBase);
1880  }
1881  return getVTableAddressPoint(Base, VTableClass);
1882 }
1883 
1884 llvm::Constant *
1885 ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPoint(BaseSubobject Base,
1886  const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass) {
1887  llvm::GlobalValue *VTable = getAddrOfVTable(VTableClass, CharUnits());
1888 
1889  // Find the appropriate vtable within the vtable group, and the address point
1890  // within that vtable.
1891  const VTableLayout &Layout =
1892  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(VTableClass);
1893  VTableLayout::AddressPointLocation AddressPoint =
1894  Layout.getAddressPoint(Base);
1895  llvm::Value *Indices[] = {
1896  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 0),
1897  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, AddressPoint.VTableIndex),
1898  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, AddressPoint.AddressPointIndex),
1899  };
1900 
1901  // Add inrange attribute to indicate that only the VTableIndex can be
1902  // accessed.
1903  unsigned ComponentSize =
1904  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(CGM.getVTableComponentType());
1905  unsigned VTableSize =
1906  ComponentSize * Layout.getVTableSize(AddressPoint.VTableIndex);
1907  unsigned Offset = ComponentSize * AddressPoint.AddressPointIndex;
1908  llvm::ConstantRange InRange(llvm::APInt(32, -Offset, true),
1909  llvm::APInt(32, VTableSize - Offset, true));
1910  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(
1911  VTable->getValueType(), VTable, Indices, /*InBounds=*/true, InRange);
1912 }
1913 
1914 // Check whether all the non-inline virtual methods for the class have the
1915 // specified attribute.
1916 template <typename T>
1917 static bool CXXRecordAllNonInlineVirtualsHaveAttr(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1918  bool FoundNonInlineVirtualMethodWithAttr = false;
1919  for (const auto *D : RD->noload_decls()) {
1920  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
1921  if (!FD->isVirtualAsWritten() || FD->isInlineSpecified() ||
1922  FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody())
1923  continue;
1924  if (!D->hasAttr<T>())
1925  return false;
1926  FoundNonInlineVirtualMethodWithAttr = true;
1927  }
1928  }
1929 
1930  // We didn't find any non-inline virtual methods missing the attribute. We
1931  // will return true when we found at least one non-inline virtual with the
1932  // attribute. (This lets our caller know that the attribute needs to be
1933  // propagated up to the vtable.)
1934  return FoundNonInlineVirtualMethodWithAttr;
1935 }
1936 
1937 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPointInStructorWithVTT(
1938  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass, BaseSubobject Base,
1939  const CXXRecordDecl *NearestVBase) {
1940  assert((Base.getBase()->getNumVBases() || NearestVBase != nullptr) &&
1941  NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD) && "This class doesn't have VTT");
1942 
1943  // Get the secondary vpointer index.
1944  uint64_t VirtualPointerIndex =
1945  CGM.getVTables().getSecondaryVirtualPointerIndex(VTableClass, Base);
1946 
1947  /// Load the VTT.
1948  llvm::Value *VTT = CGF.LoadCXXVTT();
1949  if (VirtualPointerIndex)
1950  VTT = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(CGF.GlobalsVoidPtrTy, VTT,
1951  VirtualPointerIndex);
1952 
1953  // And load the address point from the VTT.
1954  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CGF.GlobalsVoidPtrTy, VTT,
1955  CGF.getPointerAlign());
1956 }
1957 
1958 llvm::GlobalVariable *ItaniumCXXABI::getAddrOfVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
1959  CharUnits VPtrOffset) {
1960  assert(VPtrOffset.isZero() && "Itanium ABI only supports zero vptr offsets");
1961 
1962  llvm::GlobalVariable *&VTable = VTables[RD];
1963  if (VTable)
1964  return VTable;
1965 
1966  // Queue up this vtable for possible deferred emission.
1967  CGM.addDeferredVTable(RD);
1968 
1969  SmallString<256> Name;
1970  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
1971  getMangleContext().mangleCXXVTable(RD, Out);
1972 
1973  const VTableLayout &VTLayout =
1974  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
1975  llvm::Type *VTableType = CGM.getVTables().getVTableType(VTLayout);
1976 
1977  // Use pointer to global alignment for the vtable. Otherwise we would align
1978  // them based on the size of the initializer which doesn't make sense as only
1979  // single values are read.
1980  LangAS AS = CGM.GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(nullptr);
1981  unsigned PAlign = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()
1982  ? 32
1983  : CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(AS);
1984 
1985  VTable = CGM.CreateOrReplaceCXXRuntimeVariable(
1986  Name, VTableType, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
1987  getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(PAlign).getAsAlign());
1988  VTable->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
1989 
1990  // In MS C++ if you have a class with virtual functions in which you are using
1991  // selective member import/export, then all virtual functions must be exported
1992  // unless they are inline, otherwise a link error will result. To match this
1993  // behavior, for such classes, we dllimport the vtable if it is defined
1994  // externally and all the non-inline virtual methods are marked dllimport, and
1995  // we dllexport the vtable if it is defined in this TU and all the non-inline
1996  // virtual methods are marked dllexport.
1997  if (CGM.getTarget().hasPS4DLLImportExport()) {
1998  if ((!RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) && (!RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())) {
1999  if (CGM.getVTables().isVTableExternal(RD)) {
2000  if (CXXRecordAllNonInlineVirtualsHaveAttr<DLLImportAttr>(RD))
2001  VTable->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
2002  } else {
2003  if (CXXRecordAllNonInlineVirtualsHaveAttr<DLLExportAttr>(RD))
2004  VTable->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
2005  }
2006  }
2007  }
2008  CGM.setGVProperties(VTable, RD);
2009 
2010  return VTable;
2011 }
2012 
2013 CGCallee ItaniumCXXABI::getVirtualFunctionPointer(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2014  GlobalDecl GD, Address This,
2015  llvm::Type *Ty,
2016  SourceLocation Loc) {
2017  llvm::Type *PtrTy = CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy;
2018  auto *MethodDecl = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2019  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(This, PtrTy, MethodDecl->getParent());
2020 
2021  uint64_t VTableIndex = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(GD);
2022  llvm::Value *VFunc;
2023  if (CGF.ShouldEmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(MethodDecl->getParent())) {
2024  VFunc = CGF.EmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(
2025  MethodDecl->getParent(), VTable, PtrTy,
2026  VTableIndex *
2027  CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default) /
2028  8);
2029  } else {
2030  CGF.EmitTypeMetadataCodeForVCall(MethodDecl->getParent(), VTable, Loc);
2031 
2032  llvm::Value *VFuncLoad;
2033  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
2034  VFuncLoad = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(
2035  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::load_relative, {CGM.Int32Ty}),
2036  {VTable, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 4 * VTableIndex)});
2037  } else {
2038  llvm::Value *VTableSlotPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(
2039  PtrTy, VTable, VTableIndex, "vfn");
2040  VFuncLoad = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PtrTy, VTableSlotPtr,
2041  CGF.getPointerAlign());
2042  }
2043 
2044  // Add !invariant.load md to virtual function load to indicate that
2045  // function didn't change inside vtable.
2046  // It's safe to add it without -fstrict-vtable-pointers, but it would not
2047  // help in devirtualization because it will only matter if we will have 2
2048  // the same virtual function loads from the same vtable load, which won't
2049  // happen without enabled devirtualization with -fstrict-vtable-pointers.
2050  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
2051  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2052  if (auto *VFuncLoadInstr = dyn_cast<llvm::Instruction>(VFuncLoad)) {
2053  VFuncLoadInstr->setMetadata(
2054  llvm::LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load,
2055  llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2056  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Metadata *>()));
2057  }
2058  }
2059  VFunc = VFuncLoad;
2060  }
2061 
2062  CGCallee Callee(GD, VFunc);
2063  return Callee;
2064 }
2065 
2066 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitVirtualDestructorCall(
2067  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor, CXXDtorType DtorType,
2068  Address This, DeleteOrMemberCallExpr E) {
2069  auto *CE = E.dyn_cast<const CXXMemberCallExpr *>();
2070  auto *D = E.dyn_cast<const CXXDeleteExpr *>();
2071  assert((CE != nullptr) ^ (D != nullptr));
2072  assert(CE == nullptr || CE->arg_begin() == CE->arg_end());
2073  assert(DtorType == Dtor_Deleting || DtorType == Dtor_Complete);
2074 
2075  GlobalDecl GD(Dtor, DtorType);
2076  const CGFunctionInfo *FInfo =
2077  &CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXStructorDeclaration(GD);
2078  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(*FInfo);
2079  CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forVirtual(CE, GD, This, Ty);
2080 
2081  QualType ThisTy;
2082  if (CE) {
2083  ThisTy = CE->getObjectType();
2084  } else {
2085  ThisTy = D->getDestroyedType();
2086  }
2087 
2088  CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, This.emitRawPointer(CGF), ThisTy,
2089  nullptr, QualType(), nullptr);
2090  return nullptr;
2091 }
2092 
2093 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitVirtualInheritanceTables(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2094  CodeGenVTables &VTables = CGM.getVTables();
2095  llvm::GlobalVariable *VTT = VTables.GetAddrOfVTT(RD);
2096  VTables.EmitVTTDefinition(VTT, CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD), RD);
2097 }
2098 
2099 bool ItaniumCXXABI::canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(
2100  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
2101  // We don't emit available_externally vtables if we are in -fapple-kext mode
2102  // because kext mode does not permit devirtualization.
2103  if (CGM.getLangOpts().AppleKext)
2104  return false;
2105 
2106  // If the vtable is hidden then it is not safe to emit an available_externally
2107  // copy of vtable.
2108  if (isVTableHidden(RD))
2109  return false;
2110 
2111  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ForceEmitVTables)
2112  return true;
2113 
2114  // If we don't have any not emitted inline virtual function then we are safe
2115  // to emit an available_externally copy of vtable.
2116  // FIXME we can still emit a copy of the vtable if we
2117  // can emit definition of the inline functions.
2118  if (hasAnyUnusedVirtualInlineFunction(RD))
2119  return false;
2120 
2121  // For a class with virtual bases, we must also be able to speculatively
2122  // emit the VTT, because CodeGen doesn't have separate notions of "can emit
2123  // the vtable" and "can emit the VTT". For a base subobject, this means we
2124  // need to be able to emit non-virtual base vtables.
2125  if (RD->getNumVBases()) {
2126  for (const auto &B : RD->bases()) {
2127  auto *BRD = B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2128  assert(BRD && "no class for base specifier");
2129  if (B.isVirtual() || !BRD->isDynamicClass())
2130  continue;
2131  if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(BRD))
2132  return false;
2133  }
2134  }
2135 
2136  return true;
2137 }
2138 
2139 bool ItaniumCXXABI::canSpeculativelyEmitVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
2140  if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(RD))
2141  return false;
2142 
2143  // For a complete-object vtable (or more specifically, for the VTT), we need
2144  // to be able to speculatively emit the vtables of all dynamic virtual bases.
2145  for (const auto &B : RD->vbases()) {
2146  auto *BRD = B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2147  assert(BRD && "no class for base specifier");
2148  if (!BRD->isDynamicClass())
2149  continue;
2150  if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(BRD))
2151  return false;
2152  }
2153 
2154  return true;
2155 }
2156 static llvm::Value *performTypeAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2157  Address InitialPtr,
2158  int64_t NonVirtualAdjustment,
2159  int64_t VirtualAdjustment,
2160  bool IsReturnAdjustment) {
2161  if (!NonVirtualAdjustment && !VirtualAdjustment)
2162  return InitialPtr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2163 
2164  Address V = InitialPtr.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
2165 
2166  // In a base-to-derived cast, the non-virtual adjustment is applied first.
2167  if (NonVirtualAdjustment && !IsReturnAdjustment) {
2168  V = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(V,
2169  CharUnits::fromQuantity(NonVirtualAdjustment));
2170  }
2171 
2172  // Perform the virtual adjustment if we have one.
2173  llvm::Value *ResultPtr;
2174  if (VirtualAdjustment) {
2175  Address VTablePtrPtr = V.withElementType(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
2176  llvm::Value *VTablePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VTablePtrPtr);
2177 
2178  llvm::Value *Offset;
2179  llvm::Value *OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(
2180  CGF.Int8Ty, VTablePtr, VirtualAdjustment);
2181  if (CGF.CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
2182  // Load the adjustment offset from the vtable as a 32-bit int.
2183  Offset =
2184  CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CGF.Int32Ty, OffsetPtr,
2185  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
2186  } else {
2187  llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
2188  CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
2189 
2190  // Load the adjustment offset from the vtable.
2191  Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PtrDiffTy, OffsetPtr,
2192  CGF.getPointerAlign());
2193  }
2194  // Adjust our pointer.
2195  ResultPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(V.getElementType(),
2196  V.emitRawPointer(CGF), Offset);
2197  } else {
2198  ResultPtr = V.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2199  }
2200 
2201  // In a derived-to-base conversion, the non-virtual adjustment is
2202  // applied second.
2203  if (NonVirtualAdjustment && IsReturnAdjustment) {
2204  ResultPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(CGF.Int8Ty, ResultPtr,
2205  NonVirtualAdjustment);
2206  }
2207 
2208  return ResultPtr;
2209 }
2210 
2211 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::performThisAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2212  Address This,
2213  const ThisAdjustment &TA) {
2214  return performTypeAdjustment(CGF, This, TA.NonVirtual,
2215  TA.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset,
2216  /*IsReturnAdjustment=*/false);
2217 }
2218 
2219 llvm::Value *
2220 ItaniumCXXABI::performReturnAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Ret,
2221  const ReturnAdjustment &RA) {
2222  return performTypeAdjustment(CGF, Ret, RA.NonVirtual,
2223  RA.Virtual.Itanium.VBaseOffsetOffset,
2224  /*IsReturnAdjustment=*/true);
2225 }
