2227 void ARMCXXABI::EmitReturnFromThunk(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2228  RValue RV, QualType ResultType) {
2229  if (!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl()))
2230  return ItaniumCXXABI::EmitReturnFromThunk(CGF, RV, ResultType);
2231 
2232  // Destructor thunks in the ARM ABI have indeterminate results.
2233  llvm::Type *T = CGF.ReturnValue.getElementType();
2234  RValue Undef = RValue::get(llvm::UndefValue::get(T));
2235  return ItaniumCXXABI::EmitReturnFromThunk(CGF, Undef, ResultType);
2236 }
2237 
2238 /************************** Array allocation cookies **************************/
2239 
2240 CharUnits ItaniumCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(QualType elementType) {
2241  // The array cookie is a size_t; pad that up to the element alignment.
2242  // The cookie is actually right-justified in that space.
2243  return std::max(CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.SizeSizeInBytes),
2244  CGM.getContext().getPreferredTypeAlignInChars(elementType));
2245 }
2246 
2247 Address ItaniumCXXABI::InitializeArrayCookie(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2248  Address NewPtr,
2249  llvm::Value *NumElements,
2250  const CXXNewExpr *expr,
2251  QualType ElementType) {
2252  assert(requiresArrayCookie(expr));
2253 
2254  unsigned AS = NewPtr.getAddressSpace();
2255 
2256  ASTContext &Ctx = getContext();
2257  CharUnits SizeSize = CGF.getSizeSize();
2258 
2259  // The size of the cookie.
2260  CharUnits CookieSize =
2261  std::max(SizeSize, Ctx.getPreferredTypeAlignInChars(ElementType));
2262  assert(CookieSize == getArrayCookieSizeImpl(ElementType));
2263 
2264  // Compute an offset to the cookie.
2265  Address CookiePtr = NewPtr;
2266  CharUnits CookieOffset = CookieSize - SizeSize;
2267  if (!CookieOffset.isZero())
2268  CookiePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(CookiePtr, CookieOffset);
2269 
2270  // Write the number of elements into the appropriate slot.
2271  Address NumElementsPtr = CookiePtr.withElementType(CGF.SizeTy);
2272  llvm::Instruction *SI = CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NumElements, NumElementsPtr);
2273 
2274  // Handle the array cookie specially in ASan.
2275  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) && AS == 0 &&
2276  (expr->getOperatorNew()->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction() ||
2277  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeAddressPoisonCustomArrayCookie)) {
2278  // The store to the CookiePtr does not need to be instrumented.
2279  SI->setNoSanitizeMetadata();
2280  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
2281  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, NumElementsPtr.getType(), false);
2282  llvm::FunctionCallee F =
2283  CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__asan_poison_cxx_array_cookie");
2284  CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, NumElementsPtr.emitRawPointer(CGF));
2285  }
2286 
2287  // Finally, compute a pointer to the actual data buffer by skipping
2288  // over the cookie completely.
2289  return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(NewPtr, CookieSize);
2290 }
2291 
2292 llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::readArrayCookieImpl(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2293  Address allocPtr,
2294  CharUnits cookieSize) {
2295  // The element size is right-justified in the cookie.
2296  Address numElementsPtr = allocPtr;
2297  CharUnits numElementsOffset = cookieSize - CGF.getSizeSize();
2298  if (!numElementsOffset.isZero())
2299  numElementsPtr =
2300  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(numElementsPtr, numElementsOffset);
2301 
2302  unsigned AS = allocPtr.getAddressSpace();
2303  numElementsPtr = numElementsPtr.withElementType(CGF.SizeTy);
2304  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) || AS != 0)
2305  return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(numElementsPtr);
2306  // In asan mode emit a function call instead of a regular load and let the
2307  // run-time deal with it: if the shadow is properly poisoned return the
2308  // cookie, otherwise return 0 to avoid an infinite loop calling DTORs.
2309  // We can't simply ignore this load using nosanitize metadata because
2310  // the metadata may be lost.
2311  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
2312  CGF.SizeTy, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()), false);
2313  llvm::FunctionCallee F =
2314  CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__asan_load_cxx_array_cookie");
2315  return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, numElementsPtr.emitRawPointer(CGF));
2316 }
2317 
2318 CharUnits ARMCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(QualType elementType) {
2319  // ARM says that the cookie is always:
2320  // struct array_cookie {
2321  // std::size_t element_size; // element_size != 0
2322  // std::size_t element_count;
2323  // };
2324  // But the base ABI doesn't give anything an alignment greater than
2325  // 8, so we can dismiss this as typical ABI-author blindness to
2326  // actual language complexity and round up to the element alignment.
2327  return std::max(CharUnits::fromQuantity(2 * CGM.SizeSizeInBytes),
2328  CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(elementType));
2329 }
2330 
2331 Address ARMCXXABI::InitializeArrayCookie(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2332  Address newPtr,
2333  llvm::Value *numElements,
2334  const CXXNewExpr *expr,
2335  QualType elementType) {
2336  assert(requiresArrayCookie(expr));
2337 
2338  // The cookie is always at the start of the buffer.
2339  Address cookie = newPtr;
2340 
2341  // The first element is the element size.
2342  cookie = cookie.withElementType(CGF.SizeTy);
2343  llvm::Value *elementSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy,
2344  getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType).getQuantity());
2345  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(elementSize, cookie);
2346 
2347  // The second element is the element count.
2348  cookie = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(cookie, 1);
2349  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(numElements, cookie);
2350 
2351  // Finally, compute a pointer to the actual data buffer by skipping
2352  // over the cookie completely.
2353  CharUnits cookieSize = ARMCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(elementType);
2354  return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(newPtr, cookieSize);
2355 }
2356 
2357 llvm::Value *ARMCXXABI::readArrayCookieImpl(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2358  Address allocPtr,
2359  CharUnits cookieSize) {
2360  // The number of elements is at offset sizeof(size_t) relative to
2361  // the allocated pointer.
2362  Address numElementsPtr
2363  = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(allocPtr, CGF.getSizeSize());
2364 
2365  numElementsPtr = numElementsPtr.withElementType(CGF.SizeTy);
2366  return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(numElementsPtr);
2367 }

2408 namespace {

2419 
2420 /// The ARM code here follows the Itanium code closely enough that we
2421 /// just special-case it at particular places.
2422 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitGuardedInit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2423  const VarDecl &D,
2424  llvm::GlobalVariable *var,
2425  bool shouldPerformInit) {
2426  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2427 
2428  // Inline variables that weren't instantiated from variable templates have
2429  // partially-ordered initialization within their translation unit.
2430  bool NonTemplateInline =
2431  D.isInline() &&
2432  !isTemplateInstantiation(D.getTemplateSpecializationKind());
2433 
2434  // We only need to use thread-safe statics for local non-TLS variables and
2435  // inline variables; other global initialization is always single-threaded
2436  // or (through lazy dynamic loading in multiple threads) unsequenced.
2437  bool threadsafe = getContext().getLangOpts().ThreadsafeStatics &&
2438  (D.isLocalVarDecl() || NonTemplateInline) &&
2439  !D.getTLSKind();
2440 
2441  // If we have a global variable with internal linkage and thread-safe statics
2442  // are disabled, we can just let the guard variable be of type i8.
2443  bool useInt8GuardVariable = !threadsafe && var->hasInternalLinkage();
2444 
2445  llvm::IntegerType *guardTy;
2446  CharUnits guardAlignment;
2447  if (useInt8GuardVariable) {
2448  guardTy = CGF.Int8Ty;
2449  guardAlignment = CharUnits::One();
2450  } else {
2451  // Guard variables are 64 bits in the generic ABI and size width on ARM
2452  // (i.e. 32-bit on AArch32, 64-bit on AArch64).
2453  if (UseARMGuardVarABI) {
2454  guardTy = CGF.SizeTy;
2455  guardAlignment = CGF.getSizeAlign();
2456  } else {
2457  guardTy = CGF.Int64Ty;
2458  guardAlignment =
2459  CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlign(guardTy));
2460  }
2461  }
2462  llvm::PointerType *guardPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(
2463  CGF.CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2464  CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace());
2465 
2466  // Create the guard variable if we don't already have it (as we
2467  // might if we're double-emitting this function body).
2468  llvm::GlobalVariable *guard = CGM.getStaticLocalDeclGuardAddress(&D);
2469  if (!guard) {
2470  // Mangle the name for the guard.
2471  SmallString<256> guardName;
2472  {
2473  llvm::raw_svector_ostream out(guardName);
2474  getMangleContext().mangleStaticGuardVariable(&D, out);
2475  }
2476 
2477  // Create the guard variable with a zero-initializer.
2478  // Just absorb linkage, visibility and dll storage class from the guarded
2479  // variable.
2480  guard = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), guardTy,
2481  false, var->getLinkage(),
2482  llvm::ConstantInt::get(guardTy, 0),
2483  guardName.str());
2484  guard->setDSOLocal(var->isDSOLocal());
2485  guard->setVisibility(var->getVisibility());
2486  guard->setDLLStorageClass(var->getDLLStorageClass());
2487  // If the variable is thread-local, so is its guard variable.
2488  guard->setThreadLocalMode(var->getThreadLocalMode());
2489  guard->setAlignment(guardAlignment.getAsAlign());
2490 
2491  // The ABI says: "It is suggested that it be emitted in the same COMDAT
2492  // group as the associated data object." In practice, this doesn't work for
2493  // non-ELF and non-Wasm object formats, so only do it for ELF and Wasm.
2494  llvm::Comdat *C = var->getComdat();
2495  if (!D.isLocalVarDecl() && C &&
2496  (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() ||
2497  CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatWasm())) {
2498  guard->setComdat(C);
2499  } else if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && guard->isWeakForLinker()) {
2500  guard->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(guard->getName()));
2501  }
2502 
2503  CGM.setStaticLocalDeclGuardAddress(&D, guard);
2504  }
2505 
2506  Address guardAddr = Address(guard, guard->getValueType(), guardAlignment);
2507 
2508  // Test whether the variable has completed initialization.
2509  //
2510  // Itanium C++ ABI 3.3.2:
2511  // The following is pseudo-code showing how these functions can be used:
2512  // if (obj_guard.first_byte == 0) {
2513  // if ( __cxa_guard_acquire (&obj_guard) ) {
2514  // try {
2515  // ... initialize the object ...;
2516  // } catch (...) {
2517  // __cxa_guard_abort (&obj_guard);
2518  // throw;
2519  // }
2520  // ... queue object destructor with __cxa_atexit() ...;
2521  // __cxa_guard_release (&obj_guard);
2522  // }
2523  // }
2524  //
2525  // If threadsafe statics are enabled, but we don't have inline atomics, just
2526  // call __cxa_guard_acquire unconditionally. The "inline" check isn't
2527  // actually inline, and the user might not expect calls to __atomic libcalls.
2528 
2529  unsigned MaxInlineWidthInBits = CGF.getTarget().getMaxAtomicInlineWidth();
2530  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.end");
2531  if (!threadsafe || MaxInlineWidthInBits) {
2532  // Load the first byte of the guard variable.
2533  llvm::LoadInst *LI =
2534  Builder.CreateLoad(guardAddr.withElementType(CGM.Int8Ty));
2535 
2536  // Itanium ABI:
2537  // An implementation supporting thread-safety on multiprocessor
2538  // systems must also guarantee that references to the initialized
2539  // object do not occur before the load of the initialization flag.
2540  //
2541  // In LLVM, we do this by marking the load Acquire.
2542  if (threadsafe)
2543  LI->setAtomic(llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire);
2544 
2545  // For ARM, we should only check the first bit, rather than the entire byte:
2546  //
2547  // ARM C++ ABI 3.2.3.1:
2548  // To support the potential use of initialization guard variables
2549  // as semaphores that are the target of ARM SWP and LDREX/STREX
2550  // synchronizing instructions we define a static initialization
2551  // guard variable to be a 4-byte aligned, 4-byte word with the
2552  // following inline access protocol.
2553  // #define INITIALIZED 1
2554  // if ((obj_guard & INITIALIZED) != INITIALIZED) {
2555  // if (__cxa_guard_acquire(&obj_guard))
2556  // ...
2557  // }
2558  //
2559  // and similarly for ARM64:
2560  //
2561  // ARM64 C++ ABI 3.2.2:
2562  // This ABI instead only specifies the value bit 0 of the static guard
2563  // variable; all other bits are platform defined. Bit 0 shall be 0 when the
2564  // variable is not initialized and 1 when it is.
2565  llvm::Value *V =
2566  (UseARMGuardVarABI && !useInt8GuardVariable)
2567  ? Builder.CreateAnd(LI, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 1))
2568  : LI;
2569  llvm::Value *NeedsInit = Builder.CreateIsNull(V, "guard.uninitialized");
2570 
2571  llvm::BasicBlock *InitCheckBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.check");
2572 
2573  // Check if the first byte of the guard variable is zero.
2574  CGF.EmitCXXGuardedInitBranch(NeedsInit, InitCheckBlock, EndBlock,
2575  CodeGenFunction::GuardKind::VariableGuard, &D);
2576 
2577  CGF.EmitBlock(InitCheckBlock);
2578  }
2579 
2580  // The semantics of dynamic initialization of variables with static or thread
2581  // storage duration depends on whether they are declared at block-scope. The
2582  // initialization of such variables at block-scope can be aborted with an
2583  // exception and later retried (per C++20 [stmt.dcl]p4), and recursive entry
2584  // to their initialization has undefined behavior (also per C++20
2585  // [stmt.dcl]p4). For such variables declared at non-block scope, exceptions
2586  // lead to termination (per C++20 [except.terminate]p1), and recursive
2587  // references to the variables are governed only by the lifetime rules (per
2588  // C++20 [class.cdtor]p2), which means such references are perfectly fine as
2589  // long as they avoid touching memory. As a result, block-scope variables must
2590  // not be marked as initialized until after initialization completes (unless
2591  // the mark is reverted following an exception), but non-block-scope variables
2592  // must be marked prior to initialization so that recursive accesses during
2593  // initialization do not restart initialization.
2594 
2595  // Variables used when coping with thread-safe statics and exceptions.
2596  if (threadsafe) {
2597  // Call __cxa_guard_acquire.
2598  llvm::Value *V
2599  = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGuardAcquireFn(CGM, guardPtrTy), guard);
2600 
2601  llvm::BasicBlock *InitBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init");
2602 
2603  Builder.CreateCondBr(Builder.CreateIsNotNull(V, "tobool"),
2604  InitBlock, EndBlock);
2605 
2606  // Call __cxa_guard_abort along the exceptional edge.
2607  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallGuardAbort>(EHCleanup, guard);
2608 
2609  CGF.EmitBlock(InitBlock);
2610  } else if (!D.isLocalVarDecl()) {
2611  // For non-local variables, store 1 into the first byte of the guard
2612  // variable before the object initialization begins so that references
2613  // to the variable during initialization don't restart initialization.
2614  Builder.CreateStore(llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 1),
2615  guardAddr.withElementType(CGM.Int8Ty));
2616  }
2617 
2618  // Emit the initializer and add a global destructor if appropriate.
2619  CGF.EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInit(D, var, shouldPerformInit);
2620 
2621  if (threadsafe) {
2622  // Pop the guard-abort cleanup if we pushed one.
2623  CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
2624 
2625  // Call __cxa_guard_release. This cannot throw.
2626  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGuardReleaseFn(CGM, guardPtrTy),
2627  guardAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF));
2628  } else if (D.isLocalVarDecl()) {
2629  // For local variables, store 1 into the first byte of the guard variable
2630  // after the object initialization completes so that initialization is
2631  // retried if initialization is interrupted by an exception.
2632  Builder.CreateStore(llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 1),
2633  guardAddr.withElementType(CGM.Int8Ty));
2634  }
2635 
2636  CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
2637 }
2638 
2639 /// Register a global destructor using __cxa_atexit.
2640 static void emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2641  llvm::FunctionCallee dtor,
2642  llvm::Constant *addr, bool TLS) {
2643  assert(!CGF.getTarget().getTriple().isOSAIX() &&
2644  "unexpected call to emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit");
2645  assert((TLS || CGF.getTypes().getCodeGenOpts().CXAAtExit) &&
2646  "__cxa_atexit is disabled");
2647  const char *Name = "__cxa_atexit";
2648  if (TLS) {
2649  const llvm::Triple &T = CGF.getTarget().getTriple();
2650  Name = T.isOSDarwin() ? "_tlv_atexit" : "__cxa_thread_atexit";
2651  }
2652 
2653  // We're assuming that the destructor function is something we can
2654  // reasonably call with the default CC.
2655  llvm::Type *dtorTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext());
2656 
2657  // Preserve address space of addr.
2658  auto AddrAS = addr ? addr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() : 0;
2659  auto AddrPtrTy = AddrAS ? llvm::PointerType::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), AddrAS)
2660  : CGF.Int8PtrTy;
2661 
2662  // Create a variable that binds the atexit to this shared object.
2663  llvm::Constant *handle =
2664  CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(CGF.Int8Ty, "__dso_handle");
2665  auto *GV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(handle->stripPointerCasts());
2666  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
2667 
2668  // extern "C" int __cxa_atexit(void (*f)(void *), void *p, void *d);
2669  llvm::Type *paramTys[] = {dtorTy, AddrPtrTy, handle->getType()};
2670  llvm::FunctionType *atexitTy =
2671  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.IntTy, paramTys, false);
2672 
2673  // Fetch the actual function.
2674  llvm::FunctionCallee atexit = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(atexitTy, Name);
2675  if (llvm::Function *fn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(atexit.getCallee()))
2676  fn->setDoesNotThrow();
2677 
2678  if (!addr)
2679  // addr is null when we are trying to register a dtor annotated with
2680  // __attribute__((destructor)) in a constructor function. Using null here is
2681  // okay because this argument is just passed back to the destructor
2682  // function.
2683  addr = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
2684 
2685  llvm::Value *args[] = {dtor.getCallee(), addr, handle};
2686  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(atexit, args);
2687 }
2688 
2689 static llvm::Function *createGlobalInitOrCleanupFn(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
2690  StringRef FnName) {
2691  // Create a function that registers/unregisters destructors that have the same
2692  // priority.
2693  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, false);
2694  llvm::Function *GlobalInitOrCleanupFn = CGM.CreateGlobalInitOrCleanUpFunction(
2695  FTy, FnName, CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(), SourceLocation());
2696 
2697  return GlobalInitOrCleanupFn;
2698 }
2699 
2700 void CodeGenModule::unregisterGlobalDtorsWithUnAtExit() {
2701  for (const auto &I : DtorsUsingAtExit) {
2702  int Priority = I.first;
2703  std::string GlobalCleanupFnName =
2704  std::string("__GLOBAL_cleanup_") + llvm::to_string(Priority);
2705 
2706  llvm::Function *GlobalCleanupFn =
2707  createGlobalInitOrCleanupFn(*this, GlobalCleanupFnName);
2708 
2709  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
2710  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), getContext().VoidTy, GlobalCleanupFn,
2711  getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(), FunctionArgList(),
2712  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation());
2713  auto AL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
2714 
2715  // Get the destructor function type, void(*)(void).
2716  llvm::FunctionType *dtorFuncTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, false);
2717 
2718  // Destructor functions are run/unregistered in non-ascending
2719  // order of their priorities.
2720  const llvm::TinyPtrVector<llvm::Function *> &Dtors = I.second;
2721  auto itv = Dtors.rbegin();
2722  while (itv != Dtors.rend()) {
2723  llvm::Function *Dtor = *itv;
2724 
2725  // We're assuming that the destructor function is something we can
2726  // reasonably call with the correct CC.
2727  llvm::Value *V = CGF.unregisterGlobalDtorWithUnAtExit(Dtor);
2728  llvm::Value *NeedsDestruct =
2729  CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(V, "needs_destruct");
2730 
2731  llvm::BasicBlock *DestructCallBlock =
2732  CGF.createBasicBlock("destruct.call");
2733  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock(
2734  (itv + 1) != Dtors.rend() ? "unatexit.call" : "destruct.end");
2735  // Check if unatexit returns a value of 0. If it does, jump to
2736  // DestructCallBlock, otherwise jump to EndBlock directly.
2737  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(NeedsDestruct, DestructCallBlock, EndBlock);
2738 
2739  CGF.EmitBlock(DestructCallBlock);
2740 
2741  // Emit the call to casted Dtor.
2742  llvm::CallInst *CI = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(dtorFuncTy, Dtor);
2743  // Make sure the call and the callee agree on calling convention.
2744  CI->setCallingConv(Dtor->getCallingConv());
2745 
2746  CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
2747 
2748  itv++;
2749  }
2750 
2751  CGF.FinishFunction();
2752  AddGlobalDtor(GlobalCleanupFn, Priority);
2753  }
2754 }
2755 
2756 void CodeGenModule::registerGlobalDtorsWithAtExit() {
2757  for (const auto &I : DtorsUsingAtExit) {
2758  int Priority = I.first;
2759  std::string GlobalInitFnName =
2760  std::string("__GLOBAL_init_") + llvm::to_string(Priority);
2761  llvm::Function *GlobalInitFn =
2762  createGlobalInitOrCleanupFn(*this, GlobalInitFnName);
2763 
2764  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
2765  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), getContext().VoidTy, GlobalInitFn,
2766  getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(), FunctionArgList(),
2767  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation());
2768  auto AL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
2769 
2770  // Since constructor functions are run in non-descending order of their
2771  // priorities, destructors are registered in non-descending order of their
2772  // priorities, and since destructor functions are run in the reverse order
2773  // of their registration, destructor functions are run in non-ascending
2774  // order of their priorities.
2775  const llvm::TinyPtrVector<llvm::Function *> &Dtors = I.second;
2776  for (auto *Dtor : Dtors) {
2777  // Register the destructor function calling __cxa_atexit if it is
2778  // available. Otherwise fall back on calling atexit.
2779  if (getCodeGenOpts().CXAAtExit) {
2780  emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CGF, Dtor, nullptr, false);
2781  } else {
2782  // We're assuming that the destructor function is something we can
2783  // reasonably call with the correct CC.
2784  CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithAtExit(Dtor);
2785  }
2786  }
2787 
2788  CGF.FinishFunction();
2789  AddGlobalCtor(GlobalInitFn, Priority);
2790  }
2791 
2792  if (getCXXABI().useSinitAndSterm())
2793  unregisterGlobalDtorsWithUnAtExit();
2794 }
2795 
2796 /// Register a global destructor as best as we know how.
2797 void ItaniumCXXABI::registerGlobalDtor(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl &D,
2798  llvm::FunctionCallee dtor,
2799  llvm::Constant *addr) {
2800  if (D.isNoDestroy(CGM.getContext()))
2801  return;
2802 
2803  // OpenMP offloading supports C++ constructors and destructors but we do not
2804  // always have 'atexit' available. Instead lower these to use the LLVM global
2805  // destructors which we can handle directly in the runtime. Note that this is
2806  // not strictly 1-to-1 with using `atexit` because we no longer tear down
2807  // globals in reverse order of when they were constructed.
2808  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().hasAtExit() && !D.isStaticLocal())
2809  return CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithLLVM(D, dtor, addr);
2810 
2811  // emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit will emit a call to either __cxa_thread_atexit
2812  // or __cxa_atexit depending on whether this VarDecl is a thread-local storage
2813  // or not. CXAAtExit controls only __cxa_atexit, so use it if it is enabled.
2814  // We can always use __cxa_thread_atexit.
2815  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CXAAtExit || D.getTLSKind())
2816  return emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CGF, dtor, addr, D.getTLSKind());
2817 
2818  // In Apple kexts, we want to add a global destructor entry.
2819  // FIXME: shouldn't this be guarded by some variable?
2820  if (CGM.getLangOpts().AppleKext) {
2821  // Generate a global destructor entry.
2822  return CGM.AddCXXDtorEntry(dtor, addr);
2823  }
2824 
2825  CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithAtExit(D, dtor, addr);
2826 }
2827 
2828 static bool isThreadWrapperReplaceable(const VarDecl *VD,
2829  CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2830  assert(!VD->isStaticLocal() && "static local VarDecls don't need wrappers!");
2831  // Darwin prefers to have references to thread local variables to go through
2832  // the thread wrapper instead of directly referencing the backing variable.
2833  return VD->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
2834  CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin();
2835 }
2836 
2837 /// Get the appropriate linkage for the wrapper function. This is essentially
2838 /// the weak form of the variable's linkage; every translation unit which needs
2839 /// the wrapper emits a copy, and we want the linker to merge them.
2840 static llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
2841 getThreadLocalWrapperLinkage(const VarDecl *VD, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2842  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes VarLinkage =
2843  CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD);
2844 
2845  // For internal linkage variables, we don't need an external or weak wrapper.
2846  if (llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(VarLinkage))
2847  return VarLinkage;
2848 
2849  // If the thread wrapper is replaceable, give it appropriate linkage.
2850  if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM))
2851  if (!llvm::GlobalVariable::isLinkOnceLinkage(VarLinkage) &&
2852  !llvm::GlobalVariable::isWeakODRLinkage(VarLinkage))
2853  return VarLinkage;
2854  return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
2855 }
2856 
2857 llvm::Function *
2858 ItaniumCXXABI::getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(const VarDecl *VD,
2859  llvm::Value *Val) {
2860  // Mangle the name for the thread_local wrapper function.
2861  SmallString<256> WrapperName;
2862  {
2863  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(WrapperName);
2864  getMangleContext().mangleItaniumThreadLocalWrapper(VD, Out);
2865  }
2866 
2867  // FIXME: If VD is a definition, we should regenerate the function attributes
2868  // before returning.
2869  if (llvm::Value *V = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(WrapperName))
2870  return cast<llvm::Function>(V);
2871 
2872  QualType RetQT = VD->getType();
2873  if (RetQT->isReferenceType())
2874  RetQT = RetQT.getNonReferenceType();
2875 
2876  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(
2877  getContext().getPointerType(RetQT), FunctionArgList());
2878 
2879  llvm::FunctionType *FnTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2880  llvm::Function *Wrapper =
2881  llvm::Function::Create(FnTy, getThreadLocalWrapperLinkage(VD, CGM),
2882  WrapperName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
2883 
2884  if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && Wrapper->isWeakForLinker())
2885  Wrapper->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Wrapper->getName()));
2886 
2887  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, Wrapper, /*IsThunk=*/false);
2888 
2889  // Always resolve references to the wrapper at link time.
2890  if (!Wrapper->hasLocalLinkage())
2891  if (!isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM) ||
2892  llvm::GlobalVariable::isLinkOnceLinkage(Wrapper->getLinkage()) ||
2893  llvm::GlobalVariable::isWeakODRLinkage(Wrapper->getLinkage()) ||
2894  VD->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
2895  Wrapper->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
2896 
2897  if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM)) {
2898  Wrapper->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2899  Wrapper->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2900  }
2901 
2902  ThreadWrappers.push_back({VD, Wrapper});
2903  return Wrapper;
2904 }
2905 
2906 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitThreadLocalInitFuncs(
2907  CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocals,
2908  ArrayRef<llvm::Function *> CXXThreadLocalInits,
2909  ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocalInitVars) {
2910  llvm::Function *InitFunc = nullptr;
2911 
2912  // Separate initializers into those with ordered (or partially-ordered)
2913  // initialization and those with unordered initialization.
2914  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Function *, 8> OrderedInits;
2915  llvm::SmallDenseMap<const VarDecl *, llvm::Function *> UnorderedInits;
2916  for (unsigned I = 0; I != CXXThreadLocalInits.size(); ++I) {
2917  if (isTemplateInstantiation(
2918  CXXThreadLocalInitVars[I]->getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
2919  UnorderedInits[CXXThreadLocalInitVars[I]->getCanonicalDecl()] =
2920  CXXThreadLocalInits[I];
2921  else
2922  OrderedInits.push_back(CXXThreadLocalInits[I]);
2923  }
2924 
2925  if (!OrderedInits.empty()) {
2926  // Generate a guarded initialization function.
2927  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
2928  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
2929  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
2930  InitFunc = CGM.CreateGlobalInitOrCleanUpFunction(FTy, "__tls_init", FI,
2931  SourceLocation(),
2932  /*TLS=*/true);
2933  llvm::GlobalVariable *Guard = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
2934  CGM.getModule(), CGM.Int8Ty, /*isConstant=*/false,
2935  llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage,
2936  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 0), "__tls_guard");
2937  Guard->setThreadLocal(true);
2938  Guard->setThreadLocalMode(CGM.GetDefaultLLVMTLSModel());
2939 
2940  CharUnits GuardAlign = CharUnits::One();
2941  Guard->setAlignment(GuardAlign.getAsAlign());
2942 
2943  CodeGenFunction(CGM).GenerateCXXGlobalInitFunc(
2944  InitFunc, OrderedInits, ConstantAddress(Guard, CGM.Int8Ty, GuardAlign));
2945  // On Darwin platforms, use CXX_FAST_TLS calling convention.
2946  if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
2947  InitFunc->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2948  InitFunc->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2949  }
2950  }
2951 
2952  // Create declarations for thread wrappers for all thread-local variables
2953  // with non-discardable definitions in this translation unit.
2954  for (const VarDecl *VD : CXXThreadLocals) {
2955  if (VD->hasDefinition() &&
2956  !isDiscardableGVALinkage(getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD))) {
2957  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = CGM.GetGlobalValue(CGM.getMangledName(VD));
2958  getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(VD, GV);
2959  }
2960  }
2961 
2962  // Emit all referenced thread wrappers.
2963  for (auto VDAndWrapper : ThreadWrappers) {
2964  const VarDecl *VD = VDAndWrapper.first;
2965  llvm::GlobalVariable *Var =
2966  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(CGM.GetGlobalValue(CGM.getMangledName(VD)));
2967  llvm::Function *Wrapper = VDAndWrapper.second;
2968 
2969  // Some targets require that all access to thread local variables go through
2970  // the thread wrapper. This means that we cannot attempt to create a thread
2971  // wrapper or a thread helper.
2972  if (!VD->hasDefinition()) {
2973  if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM)) {
2974  Wrapper->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
2975  continue;
2976  }
2977 
2978  // If this isn't a TU in which this variable is defined, the thread
2979  // wrapper is discardable.
2980  if (Wrapper->getLinkage() == llvm::Function::WeakODRLinkage)
2981  Wrapper->setLinkage(llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
2982  }
2983 
2984  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, Wrapper);
2985 
2986  // Mangle the name for the thread_local initialization function.
2987  SmallString<256> InitFnName;
2988  {
2989  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(InitFnName);
2990  getMangleContext().mangleItaniumThreadLocalInit(VD, Out);
2991  }
2992 
2993  llvm::FunctionType *InitFnTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, false);
2994 
2995  // If we have a definition for the variable, emit the initialization
2996  // function as an alias to the global Init function (if any). Otherwise,
2997  // produce a declaration of the initialization function.
2998  llvm::GlobalValue *Init = nullptr;
2999  bool InitIsInitFunc = false;
3000  bool HasConstantInitialization = false;
3001  if (!usesThreadWrapperFunction(VD)) {
3002  HasConstantInitialization = true;
3003  } else if (VD->hasDefinition()) {
3004  InitIsInitFunc = true;
3005  llvm::Function *InitFuncToUse = InitFunc;
3006  if (isTemplateInstantiation(VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
3007  InitFuncToUse = UnorderedInits.lookup(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
3008  if (InitFuncToUse)
3009  Init = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Var->getLinkage(), InitFnName.str(),
3010  InitFuncToUse);
3011  } else {
3012  // Emit a weak global function referring to the initialization function.
3013  // This function will not exist if the TU defining the thread_local
3014  // variable in question does not need any dynamic initialization for
3015  // its thread_local variables.
3016  Init = llvm::Function::Create(InitFnTy,
3017  llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalWeakLinkage,
3018  InitFnName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
3019  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
3020  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(
3021  GlobalDecl(), FI, cast<llvm::Function>(Init), /*IsThunk=*/false);
3022  }
3023 
3024  if (Init) {
3025  Init->setVisibility(Var->getVisibility());
3026  // Don't mark an extern_weak function DSO local on windows.
3027  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSWindows() || !Init->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
3028  Init->setDSOLocal(Var->isDSOLocal());
3029  }
3030 
3031  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getModule().getContext();
3032 
3033  // The linker on AIX is not happy with missing weak symbols. However,
3034  // other TUs will not know whether the initialization routine exists
3035  // so create an empty, init function to satisfy the linker.
3036  // This is needed whenever a thread wrapper function is not used, and
3037  // also when the symbol is weak.
3038  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSAIX() && VD->hasDefinition() &&
3039  isEmittedWithConstantInitializer(VD, true) &&
3040  !mayNeedDestruction(VD)) {
3041  // Init should be null. If it were non-null, then the logic above would
3042  // either be defining the function to be an alias or declaring the
3043  // function with the expectation that the definition of the variable
3044  // is elsewhere.
3045  assert(Init == nullptr && "Expected Init to be null.");
3046 
3047  llvm::Function *Func = llvm::Function::Create(
3048  InitFnTy, Var->getLinkage(), InitFnName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
3049  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
3050  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI,
3051  cast<llvm::Function>(Func),
3052  /*IsThunk=*/false);
3053  // Create a function body that just returns
3054  llvm::BasicBlock *Entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Func);
3055  CGBuilderTy Builder(CGM, Entry);
3056  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3057  }
3058 
3059  llvm::BasicBlock *Entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
3060  CGBuilderTy Builder(CGM, Entry);
3061  if (HasConstantInitialization) {
3062  // No dynamic initialization to invoke.
3063  } else if (InitIsInitFunc) {
3064  if (Init) {
3065  llvm::CallInst *CallVal = Builder.CreateCall(InitFnTy, Init);
3066  if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM)) {
3067  CallVal->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
3068  llvm::Function *Fn =
3069  cast<llvm::Function>(cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Init)->getAliasee());
3070  Fn->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
3071  }
3072  }
3073  } else if (CGM.getTriple().isOSAIX()) {
3074  // On AIX, except if constinit and also neither of class type or of
3075  // (possibly multi-dimensional) array of class type, thread_local vars
3076  // will have init routines regardless of whether they are
3077  // const-initialized. Since the routine is guaranteed to exist, we can
3078  // unconditionally call it without testing for its existance. This
3079  // avoids potentially unresolved weak symbols which the AIX linker
3080  // isn't happy with.
3081  Builder.CreateCall(InitFnTy, Init);
3082  } else {
3083  // Don't know whether we have an init function. Call it if it exists.
3084  llvm::Value *Have = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Init);
3085  llvm::BasicBlock *InitBB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
3086  llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
3087  Builder.CreateCondBr(Have, InitBB, ExitBB);
3088 
3089  Builder.SetInsertPoint(InitBB);
3090  Builder.CreateCall(InitFnTy, Init);
3091  Builder.CreateBr(ExitBB);
3092 
3093  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitBB);
3094  }
3095 
3096  // For a reference, the result of the wrapper function is a pointer to
3097  // the referenced object.
3098  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateThreadLocalAddress(Var);
3099 
3100  if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
3101  CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3102  Val = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Var->getValueType(), Val, Align);
3103  }
3104 
3105  Builder.CreateRet(Val);
3106  }
3107 }
3108 
3109 LValue ItaniumCXXABI::EmitThreadLocalVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3110  const VarDecl *VD,
3111  QualType LValType) {
3112  llvm::Value *Val = CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
3113  llvm::Function *Wrapper = getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(VD, Val);
3114 
3115  llvm::CallInst *CallVal = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(Wrapper);
3116  CallVal->setCallingConv(Wrapper->getCallingConv());
3117 
3118  LValue LV;
3119  if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
3120  LV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignRawAddrLValue(CallVal, LValType);
3121  else
3122  LV = CGF.MakeRawAddrLValue(CallVal, LValType,
3123  CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
3124  // FIXME: need setObjCGCLValueClass?
3125  return LV;
3126 }
3127 
3128 /// Return whether the given global decl needs a VTT parameter, which it does
3129 /// if it's a base constructor or destructor with virtual bases.
3130 bool ItaniumCXXABI::NeedsVTTParameter(GlobalDecl GD) {
3131  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3132 
3133  // We don't have any virtual bases, just return early.
3134  if (!MD->getParent()->getNumVBases())
3135  return false;
3136 
3137  // Check if we have a base constructor.
3138  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Base)
3139  return true;
3140 
3141  // Check if we have a base destructor.
3142  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) && GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base)
3143  return true;
3144 
3145  return false;
3146 }

3249 llvm::GlobalVariable *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::GetAddrOfTypeName(
3250  QualType Ty, llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage) {
3251  SmallString<256> Name;
3252  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3253  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIName(Ty, Out);
3254 
3255  // We know that the mangled name of the type starts at index 4 of the
3256  // mangled name of the typename, so we can just index into it in order to
3257  // get the mangled name of the type.
3258  llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext,
3259  Name.substr(4));
3260  auto Align = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(CGM.getContext().CharTy);
3261 
3262  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.CreateOrReplaceCXXRuntimeVariable(
3263  Name, Init->getType(), Linkage, Align.getAsAlign());
3264 
3265  GV->setInitializer(Init);
3266 
3267  return GV;
3268 }
3269 
3270 llvm::Constant *
3271 ItaniumRTTIBuilder::GetAddrOfExternalRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty) {
3272  // Mangle the RTTI name.
3273  SmallString<256> Name;
3274  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3275  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
3276 
3277  // Look for an existing global.
3278  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
3279 
3280  if (!GV) {
3281  // Create a new global variable.
3282  // Note for the future: If we would ever like to do deferred emission of
3283  // RTTI, check if emitting vtables opportunistically need any adjustment.
3284 
3285  GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3286  CGM.getModule(), CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy,
3287  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr, Name);
3288  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3289  CGM.setGVProperties(GV, RD);
3290  // Import the typeinfo symbol when all non-inline virtual methods are
3291  // imported.
3292  if (CGM.getTarget().hasPS4DLLImportExport()) {
3293  if (RD && CXXRecordAllNonInlineVirtualsHaveAttr<DLLImportAttr>(RD)) {
3294  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLImportStorageClass);
3295  CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
3296  }
3297  }
3298  }
3299 
3300  return GV;
3301 }
3302 
3303 /// TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary - Given a builtin type, returns whether the type
3304 /// info for that type is defined in the standard library.
3305 static bool TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(const BuiltinType *Ty) {
3306  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.2:
3307  // Basic type information (e.g. for "int", "bool", etc.) will be kept in
3308  // the run-time support library. Specifically, the run-time support
3309  // library should contain type_info objects for the types X, X* and
3310  // X const*, for every X in: void, std::nullptr_t, bool, wchar_t, char,
3311  // unsigned char, signed char, short, unsigned short, int, unsigned int,
3312  // long, unsigned long, long long, unsigned long long, float, double,
3313  // long double, char16_t, char32_t, and the IEEE 754r decimal and
3314  // half-precision floating point types.
3315  //
3316  // GCC also emits RTTI for __int128.
3317  // FIXME: We do not emit RTTI information for decimal types here.
3318 
3319  // Types added here must also be added to EmitFundamentalRTTIDescriptors.
3320  switch (Ty->getKind()) {
3321  case BuiltinType::Void:
3322  case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
3323  case BuiltinType::Bool:
3324  case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
3325  case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
3326  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
3327  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
3328  case BuiltinType::UChar:
3329  case BuiltinType::SChar:
3330  case BuiltinType::Short:
3331  case BuiltinType::UShort:
3332  case BuiltinType::Int:
3333  case BuiltinType::UInt:
3334  case BuiltinType::Long:
3335  case BuiltinType::ULong:
3336  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
3337  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
3338  case BuiltinType::Half:
3339  case BuiltinType::Float:
3340  case BuiltinType::Double:
3341  case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
3342  case BuiltinType::Float16:
3343  case BuiltinType::Float128:
3344  case BuiltinType::Ibm128:
3345  case BuiltinType::Char8:
3346  case BuiltinType::Char16:
3347  case BuiltinType::Char32:
3348  case BuiltinType::Int128:
3349  case BuiltinType::UInt128:
3350  return true;
3351 
3352 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
3353  case BuiltinType::Id:
3354 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
3355 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
3356  case BuiltinType::Sampled##Id:
3357 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
3358 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
3359 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
3360 #define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
3361  case BuiltinType::Id:
3362 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
3363  case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
3364  case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
3365  case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
3366  case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
3367  case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
3368 #define SVE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
3369  case BuiltinType::Id:
3370 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
3371 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) \
3372  case BuiltinType::Id:
3373 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
3374 #define RVV_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
3375 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
3376 #define WASM_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
3377 #include "clang/Basic/WebAssemblyReferenceTypes.def"
3378  case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
3379  case BuiltinType::Accum:
3380  case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
3381  case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
3382  case BuiltinType::UAccum:
3383  case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
3384  case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
3385  case BuiltinType::Fract:
3386  case BuiltinType::LongFract:
3387  case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
3388  case BuiltinType::UFract:
3389  case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
3390  case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
3391  case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
3392  case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
3393  case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
3394  case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
3395  case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
3396  case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
3397  case BuiltinType::SatFract:
3398  case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
3399  case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
3400  case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
3401  case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
3402  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
3403  return false;
3404 
3405  case BuiltinType::Dependent:
3406 #define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId)
3407 #define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) \
3408  case BuiltinType::Id:
3409 #include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
3410  llvm_unreachable("asking for RRTI for a placeholder type!");
3411 
3412  case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
3413  case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
3414  case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
3415  llvm_unreachable("FIXME: Objective-C types are unsupported!");
3416  }
3417 
3418  llvm_unreachable("Invalid BuiltinType Kind!");
3419 }

3421 static bool TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(const PointerType *PointerTy) {
3422  QualType PointeeTy = PointerTy->getPointeeType();
3423  const BuiltinType *BuiltinTy = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(PointeeTy);
3424  if (!BuiltinTy)
3425  return false;
3426 
3427  // Check the qualifiers.
3428  Qualifiers Quals = PointeeTy.getQualifiers();
3429  Quals.removeConst();
3430 
3431  if (!Quals.empty())
3432  return false;
3433 
3434  return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(BuiltinTy);
3435 }
3436 
3437 /// IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor - Returns whether the type
3438 /// information for the given type exists in the standard library.
3439 static bool IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty) {
3440  // Type info for builtin types is defined in the standard library.
3441  if (const BuiltinType *BuiltinTy = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(Ty))
3442  return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(BuiltinTy);
3443 
3444  // Type info for some pointer types to builtin types is defined in the
3445  // standard library.
3446  if (const PointerType *PointerTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty))
3447  return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(PointerTy);
3448 
3449  return false;
3450 }
3451 
3452 /// ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor - Returns whether the type information for
3453 /// the given type exists somewhere else, and that we should not emit the type
3454 /// information in this translation unit. Assumes that it is not a
3455 /// standard-library type.
3456 static bool ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3457  QualType Ty) {
3458  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3459 
3460  // If RTTI is disabled, assume it might be disabled in the
3461  // translation unit that defines any potential key function, too.
3462  if (!Context.getLangOpts().RTTI) return false;
3463 
3464  if (const RecordType *RecordTy = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3465  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl());
3466  if (!RD->hasDefinition())
3467  return false;
3468 
3469  if (!RD->isDynamicClass())
3470  return false;
3471 
3472  // FIXME: this may need to be reconsidered if the key function
3473  // changes.
3474  // N.B. We must always emit the RTTI data ourselves if there exists a key
3475  // function.
3476  bool IsDLLImport = RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3477 
3478  // Don't import the RTTI but emit it locally.
3479  if (CGM.getTriple().isWindowsGNUEnvironment())
3480  return false;
3481 
3482  if (CGM.getVTables().isVTableExternal(RD)) {
3483  if (CGM.getTarget().hasPS4DLLImportExport())
3484  return true;
3485 
3486  return IsDLLImport && !CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment()
3487  ? false
3488  : true;
3489  }
3490  if (IsDLLImport)
3491  return true;
3492  }
3493 
3494  return false;
3495 }
3496 
3497 /// IsIncompleteClassType - Returns whether the given record type is incomplete.
3498 static bool IsIncompleteClassType(const RecordType *RecordTy) {
3499  return !RecordTy->getDecl()->isCompleteDefinition();
3500 }
3501 
3502 /// ContainsIncompleteClassType - Returns whether the given type contains an
3503 /// incomplete class type. This is true if
3504 ///
3505 /// * The given type is an incomplete class type.
3506 /// * The given type is a pointer type whose pointee type contains an
3507 /// incomplete class type.
3508 /// * The given type is a member pointer type whose class is an incomplete
3509 /// class type.
3510 /// * The given type is a member pointer type whoise pointee type contains an
3511 /// incomplete class type.
3512 /// is an indirect or direct pointer to an incomplete class type.
3513 static bool ContainsIncompleteClassType(QualType Ty) {
3514  if (const RecordType *RecordTy = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3515  if (IsIncompleteClassType(RecordTy))
3516  return true;
3517  }
3518 
3519  if (const PointerType *PointerTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty))
3520  return ContainsIncompleteClassType(PointerTy->getPointeeType());
3521 
3522  if (const MemberPointerType *MemberPointerTy =
3523  dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty)) {
3524  // Check if the class type is incomplete.
3525  const RecordType *ClassType = cast<RecordType>(MemberPointerTy->getClass());
3526  if (IsIncompleteClassType(ClassType))
3527  return true;
3528 
3529  return ContainsIncompleteClassType(MemberPointerTy->getPointeeType());
3530  }
3531 
3532  return false;
3533 }
3534 
3535 // CanUseSingleInheritance - Return whether the given record decl has a "single,
3536 // public, non-virtual base at offset zero (i.e. the derived class is dynamic
3537 // iff the base is)", according to Itanium C++ ABI, 2.95p6b.
3538 static bool CanUseSingleInheritance(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3539  // Check the number of bases.
3540  if (RD->getNumBases() != 1)
3541  return false;
3542 
3543  // Get the base.
3544  CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_iterator Base = RD->bases_begin();
3545 
3546  // Check that the base is not virtual.
3547  if (Base->isVirtual())
3548  return false;
3549 
3550  // Check that the base is public.
3551  if (Base->getAccessSpecifier() != AS_public)
3552  return false;
3553 
3554  // Check that the class is dynamic iff the base is.
3555  auto *BaseDecl =
3556  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
3557  if (!BaseDecl->isEmpty() &&
3558  BaseDecl->isDynamicClass() != RD->isDynamicClass())
3559  return false;
3560 
3561  return true;
3562 }
3563 
3564 void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildVTablePointer(const Type *Ty) {
3565  // abi::__class_type_info.
3566  static const char * const ClassTypeInfo =
3567  "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv117__class_type_infoE";
3568  // abi::__si_class_type_info.
3569  static const char * const SIClassTypeInfo =
3570  "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv120__si_class_type_infoE";
3571  // abi::__vmi_class_type_info.
3572  static const char * const VMIClassTypeInfo =
3573  "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv121__vmi_class_type_infoE";
3574 
3575  const char *VTableName = nullptr;
3576 
3577  switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
3578 #define TYPE(Class, Base)
3579 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3580 #define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3581 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3582 #define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3583 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
3584  llvm_unreachable("Non-canonical and dependent types shouldn't get here");
3585 
3586  case Type::LValueReference:
3587  case Type::RValueReference:
3588  llvm_unreachable("References shouldn't get here");
3589 
3590  case Type::Auto:
3591  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3592  llvm_unreachable("Undeduced type shouldn't get here");
3593 
3594  case Type::Pipe:
3595  llvm_unreachable("Pipe types shouldn't get here");
3596 
3597  case Type::ArrayParameter:
3598  llvm_unreachable("Array Parameter types should not get here.");
3599 
3600  case Type::Builtin:
3601  case Type::BitInt:
3602  // GCC treats vector and complex types as fundamental types.
3603  case Type::Vector:
3604  case Type::ExtVector:
3605  case Type::ConstantMatrix:
3606  case Type::Complex:
3607  case Type::Atomic:
3608  // FIXME: GCC treats block pointers as fundamental types?!
3609  case Type::BlockPointer:
3610  // abi::__fundamental_type_info.
3611  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv123__fundamental_type_infoE";
3612  break;
3613 
3614  case Type::ConstantArray:
3615  case Type::IncompleteArray:
3616  case Type::VariableArray:
3617  // abi::__array_type_info.
3618  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv117__array_type_infoE";
3619  break;
3620 
3621  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3622  case Type::FunctionProto:
3623  // abi::__function_type_info.
3624  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv120__function_type_infoE";
3625  break;
3626 
3627  case Type::Enum:
3628  // abi::__enum_type_info.
3629  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv116__enum_type_infoE";
3630  break;
3631 
3632  case Type::Record: {
3633  const CXXRecordDecl *RD =
3634  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(cast<RecordType>(Ty)->getDecl());
3635 
3636  if (!RD->hasDefinition() || !RD->getNumBases()) {
3637  VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3638  } else if (CanUseSingleInheritance(RD)) {
3639  VTableName = SIClassTypeInfo;
3640  } else {
3641  VTableName = VMIClassTypeInfo;
3642  }
3643 
3644  break;
3645  }
3646 
3647  case Type::ObjCObject:
3648  // Ignore protocol qualifiers.
3649  Ty = cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty)->getBaseType().getTypePtr();
3650 
3651  // Handle id and Class.
3652  if (isa<BuiltinType>(Ty)) {
3653  VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3654  break;
3655  }
3656 
3657  assert(isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty));
3658  [[fallthrough]];
3659 
3660  case Type::ObjCInterface:
3661  if (cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty)->getDecl()->getSuperClass()) {
3662  VTableName = SIClassTypeInfo;
3663  } else {
3664  VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3665  }
3666  break;
3667 
3668  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3669  case Type::Pointer:
3670  // abi::__pointer_type_info.
3671  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv119__pointer_type_infoE";
3672  break;
3673 
3674  case Type::MemberPointer:
3675  // abi::__pointer_to_member_type_info.
3676  VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv129__pointer_to_member_type_infoE";
3677  break;
3678  }
3679 
3680  llvm::Constant *VTable = nullptr;
3681 
3682  // Check if the alias exists. If it doesn't, then get or create the global.
3683  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout())
3684  VTable = CGM.getModule().getNamedAlias(VTableName);
3685  if (!VTable) {
3686  llvm::Type *Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy, 0);
3687  VTable = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertGlobal(VTableName, Ty);
3688  }
3689 
3690  CGM.setDSOLocal(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(VTable->stripPointerCasts()));
3691 
3692  llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
3693  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
3694 
3695  // The vtable address point is 2.
3696  if (CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().isRelativeLayout()) {
3697  // The vtable address point is 8 bytes after its start:
3698  // 4 for the offset to top + 4 for the relative offset to rtti.
3699  llvm::Constant *Eight = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 8);
3700  VTable =
3701  llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(CGM.Int8Ty, VTable, Eight);
3702  } else {
3703  llvm::Constant *Two = llvm::ConstantInt::get(PtrDiffTy, 2);
3704  VTable = llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy,
3705  VTable, Two);
3706  }
3707 
3708  Fields.push_back(VTable);
3709 }
3710 
3711 /// Return the linkage that the type info and type info name constants
3712 /// should have for the given type.
3713 static llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes getTypeInfoLinkage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3714  QualType Ty) {
3715  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3716  // In addition, it and all of the intermediate abi::__pointer_type_info
3717  // structs in the chain down to the abi::__class_type_info for the
3718  // incomplete class type must be prevented from resolving to the
3719  // corresponding type_info structs for the complete class type, possibly
3720  // by making them local static objects. Finally, a dummy class RTTI is
3721  // generated for the incomplete type that will not resolve to the final
3722  // complete class RTTI (because the latter need not exist), possibly by
3723  // making it a local static object.
3724  if (ContainsIncompleteClassType(Ty))
3725  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3726 
3727  switch (Ty->getLinkage()) {
3728  case Linkage::Invalid:
3729  llvm_unreachable("Linkage hasn't been computed!");
3730 
3731  case Linkage::None:
3732  case Linkage::Internal:
3733  case Linkage::UniqueExternal:
3734  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3735 
3736  case Linkage::VisibleNone:
3737  case Linkage::Module:
3738  case Linkage::External:
3739  // RTTI is not enabled, which means that this type info struct is going
3740  // to be used for exception handling. Give it linkonce_odr linkage.
3741  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().RTTI)
3742  return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
3743 
3744  if (const RecordType *Record = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3745  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl());
3746  if (RD->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
3747  return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
3748  if (CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment())
3749  if (RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() &&
3750  ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CGM, Ty))
3751  return llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage;
3752  // MinGW always uses LinkOnceODRLinkage for type info.
3753  if (RD->isDynamicClass() &&
3754  !CGM.getContext()
3755  .getTargetInfo()
3756  .getTriple()
3757  .isWindowsGNUEnvironment())
3758  return CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
3759  }
3760 
3761  return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
3762  }
3763 
3764  llvm_unreachable("Invalid linkage!");
3765 }
3766 
3767 llvm::Constant *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildTypeInfo(QualType Ty) {
3768  // We want to operate on the canonical type.
3769  Ty = Ty.getCanonicalType();
3770 
3771  // Check if we've already emitted an RTTI descriptor for this type.
3772  SmallString<256> Name;
3773  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3774  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
3775 
3776  llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
3777  if (OldGV && !OldGV->isDeclaration()) {
3778  assert(!OldGV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage() &&
3779  "available_externally typeinfos not yet implemented");
3780 
3781  return OldGV;
3782  }
3783 
3784  // Check if there is already an external RTTI descriptor for this type.
3785  if (IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor(Ty) ||
3786  ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CGM, Ty))
3787  return GetAddrOfExternalRTTIDescriptor(Ty);
3788 
3789  // Emit the standard library with external linkage.
3790  llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage = getTypeInfoLinkage(CGM, Ty);
3791 
3792  // Give the type_info object and name the formal visibility of the
3793  // type itself.
3794  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes llvmVisibility;
3795  if (llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage))
3796  // If the linkage is local, only default visibility makes sense.
3797  llvmVisibility = llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility;
3798  else if (CXXABI.classifyRTTIUniqueness(Ty, Linkage) ==
3799  ItaniumCXXABI::RUK_NonUniqueHidden)
3800  llvmVisibility = llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility;
3801  else
3802  llvmVisibility = CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(Ty->getVisibility());
3803 
3804  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes DLLStorageClass =
3805  llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass;
3806  if (auto RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
3807  if ((CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment() &&
3808  RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) ||
3809  (CGM.shouldMapVisibilityToDLLExport(RD) &&
3810  !llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage) &&
3811  llvmVisibility == llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility))
3812  DLLStorageClass = llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass;
3813  }
3814  return BuildTypeInfo(Ty, Linkage, llvmVisibility, DLLStorageClass);
3815 }
3816 
3817 llvm::Constant *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildTypeInfo(
3818  QualType Ty,
3819  llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage,
3820  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes Visibility,
3821  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes DLLStorageClass) {
3822  // Add the vtable pointer.
3823  BuildVTablePointer(cast<Type>(Ty));
3824 
3825  // And the name.
3826  llvm::GlobalVariable *TypeName = GetAddrOfTypeName(Ty, Linkage);
3827  llvm::Constant *TypeNameField;
3828 
3829  // If we're supposed to demote the visibility, be sure to set a flag
3830  // to use a string comparison for type_info comparisons.
3831  ItaniumCXXABI::RTTIUniquenessKind RTTIUniqueness =
3832  CXXABI.classifyRTTIUniqueness(Ty, Linkage);
3833  if (RTTIUniqueness != ItaniumCXXABI::RUK_Unique) {
3834  // The flag is the sign bit, which on ARM64 is defined to be clear
3835  // for global pointers. This is very ARM64-specific.
3836  TypeNameField = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(TypeName, CGM.Int64Ty);
3837  llvm::Constant *flag =
3838  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int64Ty, ((uint64_t)1) << 63);
3839  TypeNameField = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAdd(TypeNameField, flag);
3840  TypeNameField =
3841  llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(TypeNameField, CGM.GlobalsInt8PtrTy);
3842  } else {
3843  TypeNameField = TypeName;
3844  }
3845  Fields.push_back(TypeNameField);
3846 
3847  switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
3848 #define TYPE(Class, Base)
3849 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3850 #define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3851 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3852 #define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3853 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
3854  llvm_unreachable("Non-canonical and dependent types shouldn't get here");
3855 
3856  // GCC treats vector types as fundamental types.
3857  case Type::Builtin:
3858  case Type::Vector:
3859  case Type::ExtVector:
3860  case Type::ConstantMatrix:
3861  case Type::Complex:
3862  case Type::BlockPointer:
3863  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p4:
3864  // abi::__fundamental_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3865  break;
3866 
3867  case Type::LValueReference:
3868  case Type::RValueReference:
3869  llvm_unreachable("References shouldn't get here");
3870 
3871  case Type::Auto:
3872  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3873  llvm_unreachable("Undeduced type shouldn't get here");
3874 
3875  case Type::Pipe:
3876  break;
3877 
3878  case Type::BitInt:
3879  break;
3880 
3881  case Type::ConstantArray:
3882  case Type::IncompleteArray:
3883  case Type::VariableArray:
3884  case Type::ArrayParameter:
3885  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3886  // abi::__array_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3887  break;
3888 
3889  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3890  case Type::FunctionProto:
3891  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3892  // abi::__function_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3893  break;
3894 
3895  case Type::Enum:
3896  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3897  // abi::__enum_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3898  break;
3899 
3900  case Type::Record: {
3901  const CXXRecordDecl *RD =
3902  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(cast<RecordType>(Ty)->getDecl());
3903  if (!RD->hasDefinition() || !RD->getNumBases()) {
3904  // We don't need to emit any fields.
3905  break;
3906  }
3907 
3908  if (CanUseSingleInheritance(RD))
3909  BuildSIClassTypeInfo(RD);
3910  else
3911  BuildVMIClassTypeInfo(RD);
3912 
3913  break;
3914  }
3915 
3916  case Type::ObjCObject:
3917  case Type::ObjCInterface:
3918  BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty));
3919  break;
3920 
3921  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3922  BuildPointerTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType());
3923  break;
3924 
3925  case Type::Pointer:
3926  BuildPointerTypeInfo(cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType());
3927  break;
3928 
3929  case Type::MemberPointer:
3930  BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo(cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty));
3931  break;
3932 
3933  case Type::Atomic:
3934  // No fields, at least for the moment.
3935  break;
3936  }
3937 
3938  llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
3939 
3940  SmallString<256> Name;
3941  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3942  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
3943  llvm::Module &M = CGM.getModule();
3944  llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = M.getNamedGlobal(Name);
3945  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3946  new llvm::GlobalVariable(M, Init->getType(),
3947  /*isConstant=*/true, Linkage, Init, Name);
3948 
3949  // Export the typeinfo in the same circumstances as the vtable is exported.
3950  auto GVDLLStorageClass = DLLStorageClass;
3951  if (CGM.getTarget().hasPS4DLLImportExport()) {
3952  if (const RecordType *RecordTy = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3953  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl());
3954  if (RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() ||
3955  CXXRecordAllNonInlineVirtualsHaveAttr<DLLExportAttr>(RD)) {
3956  GVDLLStorageClass = llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass;
3957  }
3958  }
3959  }
3960 
3961  // If there's already an old global variable, replace it with the new one.
3962  if (OldGV) {
3963  GV->takeName(OldGV);
3964  OldGV->replaceAllUsesWith(GV);
3965  OldGV->eraseFromParent();
3966  }
3967 
3968  if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker())
3969  GV->setComdat(M.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3970 
3971  CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
3972  CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(CGM.GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(nullptr)));
3973  GV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
3974 
3975  // The Itanium ABI specifies that type_info objects must be globally
3976  // unique, with one exception: if the type is an incomplete class
3977  // type or a (possibly indirect) pointer to one. That exception
3978  // affects the general case of comparing type_info objects produced
3979  // by the typeid operator, which is why the comparison operators on
3980  // std::type_info generally use the type_info name pointers instead
3981  // of the object addresses. However, the language's built-in uses
3982  // of RTTI generally require class types to be complete, even when
3983  // manipulating pointers to those class types. This allows the
3984  // implementation of dynamic_cast to rely on address equality tests,
3985  // which is much faster.
3986 
3987  // All of this is to say that it's important that both the type_info
3988  // object and the type_info name be uniqued when weakly emitted.
3989 
3990  TypeName->setVisibility(Visibility);
3991  CGM.setDSOLocal(TypeName);
3992 
3993  GV->setVisibility(Visibility);
3994  CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
3995 
3996  TypeName->setDLLStorageClass(DLLStorageClass);
3997  GV->setDLLStorageClass(CGM.getTarget().hasPS4DLLImportExport()
3998  ? GVDLLStorageClass
3999  : DLLStorageClass);
4000 
4001  TypeName->setPartition(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SymbolPartition);
4002  GV->setPartition(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SymbolPartition);
4003 
4004  return GV;
4005 }
4006 
4007 /// BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo - Build the appropriate kind of type_info
4008 /// for the given Objective-C object type.
4009 void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo(const ObjCObjectType *OT) {
4010  // Drop qualifiers.
4011  const Type *T = OT->getBaseType().getTypePtr();
4012  assert(isa<BuiltinType>(T) || isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(T));
4013 
4014  // The builtin types are abi::__class_type_infos and don't require
4015  // extra fields.
4016  if (isa<BuiltinType>(T)) return;
4017 
4018  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T)->getDecl();
4019  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Class->getSuperClass();
4020 
4021  // Root classes are also __class_type_info.
4022  if (!Super) return;
4023 
4024  QualType SuperTy = CGM.getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(Super);
4025 
4026  // Everything else is single inheritance.
4027  llvm::Constant *BaseTypeInfo =
4028  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(SuperTy);
4029  Fields.push_back(BaseTypeInfo);
4030 }
4031 
4032 /// BuildSIClassTypeInfo - Build an abi::__si_class_type_info, used for single
4033 /// inheritance, according to the Itanium C++ ABI, 2.95p6b.
4034 void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildSIClassTypeInfo(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
4035  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6b:
4036  // It adds to abi::__class_type_info a single member pointing to the
4037  // type_info structure for the base type,
4038  llvm::Constant *BaseTypeInfo =
4039  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(RD->bases_begin()->getType());
4040  Fields.push_back(BaseTypeInfo);
4041 }
4042 
4043 namespace {
4044  /// SeenBases - Contains virtual and non-virtual bases seen when traversing
4045  /// a class hierarchy.
4046  struct SeenBases {
4047  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 16> NonVirtualBases;
4048  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 16> VirtualBases;
4049  };
4050 }
4051 
4052 /// ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags - Compute the value of the flags member in
4053 /// abi::__vmi_class_type_info.
4054 ///
4055 static unsigned ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(const CXXBaseSpecifier *Base,
4056  SeenBases &Bases) {
4057 
4058  unsigned Flags = 0;
4059 
4060  auto *BaseDecl =
4061  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
4062 
4063  if (Base->isVirtual()) {
4064  // Mark the virtual base as seen.
4065  if (!Bases.VirtualBases.insert(BaseDecl).second) {
4066  // If this virtual base has been seen before, then the class is diamond
4067  // shaped.
4068  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_DiamondShaped;
4069  } else {
4070  if (Bases.NonVirtualBases.count(BaseDecl))
4071  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
4072  }
4073  } else {
4074  // Mark the non-virtual base as seen.
4075  if (!Bases.NonVirtualBases.insert(BaseDecl).second) {
4076  // If this non-virtual base has been seen before, then the class has non-
4077  // diamond shaped repeated inheritance.
4078  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
4079  } else {
4080  if (Bases.VirtualBases.count(BaseDecl))
4081  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
4082  }
4083  }
4084 
4085  // Walk all bases.
4086  for (const auto &I : BaseDecl->bases())
4087  Flags |= ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(&I, Bases);
4088 
4089  return Flags;
4090 }
4091 
4092 static unsigned ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
4093  unsigned Flags = 0;
4094  SeenBases Bases;
4095 
4096  // Walk all bases.
4097  for (const auto &I : RD->bases())
4098  Flags |= ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(&I, Bases);
4099 
4100  return Flags;
4101 }
4102 
4103 /// BuildVMIClassTypeInfo - Build an abi::__vmi_class_type_info, used for
4104 /// classes with bases that do not satisfy the abi::__si_class_type_info
4105 /// constraints, according ti the Itanium C++ ABI, 2.9.5p5c.
4106 void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildVMIClassTypeInfo(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
4107  llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
4108  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
4109 
4110  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
4111  // __flags is a word with flags describing details about the class
4112  // structure, which may be referenced by using the __flags_masks
4113  // enumeration. These flags refer to both direct and indirect bases.
4114  unsigned Flags = ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(RD);
4115  Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
4116 
4117  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
4118  // __base_count is a word with the number of direct proper base class
4119  // descriptions that follow.
4120  Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, RD->getNumBases()));
4121 
4122  if (!RD->getNumBases())
4123  return;
4124 
4125  // Now add the base class descriptions.
4126 
4127  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
4128  // __base_info[] is an array of base class descriptions -- one for every
4129  // direct proper base. Each description is of the type:
4130  //
4131  // struct abi::__base_class_type_info {
4132  // public:
4133  // const __class_type_info *__base_type;
4134  // long __offset_flags;
4135  //
4136  // enum __offset_flags_masks {
4137  // __virtual_mask = 0x1,
4138  // __public_mask = 0x2,
4139  // __offset_shift = 8
4140  // };
4141  // };
4142 
4143  // If we're in mingw and 'long' isn't wide enough for a pointer, use 'long
4144  // long' instead of 'long' for __offset_flags. libstdc++abi uses long long on
4145  // LLP64 platforms.
4146  // FIXME: Consider updating libc++abi to match, and extend this logic to all
4147  // LLP64 platforms.
4148  QualType OffsetFlagsTy = CGM.getContext().LongTy;
4149  const TargetInfo &TI = CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo();
4150  if (TI.getTriple().isOSCygMing() &&
4151  TI.getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default) > TI.getLongWidth())
4152  OffsetFlagsTy = CGM.getContext().LongLongTy;
4153  llvm::Type *OffsetFlagsLTy =
4154  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(OffsetFlagsTy);
4155 
4156  for (const auto &Base : RD->bases()) {
4157  // The __base_type member points to the RTTI for the base type.
4158  Fields.push_back(ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(Base.getType()));
4159 
4160  auto *BaseDecl =
4161  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base.getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
4162 
4163  int64_t OffsetFlags = 0;
4164 
4165  // All but the lower 8 bits of __offset_flags are a signed offset.
4166  // For a non-virtual base, this is the offset in the object of the base
4167  // subobject. For a virtual base, this is the offset in the virtual table of
4168  // the virtual base offset for the virtual base referenced (negative).
4169  CharUnits Offset;
4170  if (Base.isVirtual())
4171  Offset =
4172  CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(RD, BaseDecl);
4173  else {
4174  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
4175  Offset = Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
4176  };
4177 
4178  OffsetFlags = uint64_t(Offset.getQuantity()) << 8;
4179 
4180  // The low-order byte of __offset_flags contains flags, as given by the
4181  // masks from the enumeration __offset_flags_masks.
4182  if (Base.isVirtual())
4183  OffsetFlags |= BCTI_Virtual;
4184  if (Base.getAccessSpecifier() == AS_public)
4185  OffsetFlags |= BCTI_Public;
4186 
4187  Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(OffsetFlagsLTy, OffsetFlags));
4188  }
4189 }
4190 
4191 /// Compute the flags for a __pbase_type_info, and remove the corresponding
4192 /// pieces from \p Type.
4193 static unsigned extractPBaseFlags(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType &Type) {
4194  unsigned Flags = 0;
4195 
4196  if (Type.isConstQualified())
4197  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Const;
4198  if (Type.isVolatileQualified())
4199  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Volatile;
4200  if (Type.isRestrictQualified())
4201  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Restrict;
4202  Type = Type.getUnqualifiedType();
4203 
4204  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
4205  // When the abi::__pbase_type_info is for a direct or indirect pointer to an
4206  // incomplete class type, the incomplete target type flag is set.
4207  if (ContainsIncompleteClassType(Type))
4208  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Incomplete;
4209 
4210  if (auto *Proto = Type->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
4211  if (Proto->isNothrow()) {
4212  Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Noexcept;
4213  Type = Ctx.getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(Type, EST_None);
4214  }
4215  }
4216 
4217  return Flags;
4218 }
4219 
4220 /// BuildPointerTypeInfo - Build an abi::__pointer_type_info struct,
4221 /// used for pointer types.
4222 void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildPointerTypeInfo(QualType PointeeTy) {
4223  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
4224  // __flags is a flag word describing the cv-qualification and other
4225  // attributes of the type pointed to
4226  unsigned Flags = extractPBaseFlags(CGM.getContext(), PointeeTy);
4227 
4228  llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
4229  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
4230  Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
4231 
4232  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
4233  // __pointee is a pointer to the std::type_info derivation for the
4234  // unqualified type being pointed to.
4235  llvm::Constant *PointeeTypeInfo =
4236  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(PointeeTy);
4237  Fields.push_back(PointeeTypeInfo);
4238 }

4240 /// BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo - Build an abi::__pointer_to_member_type_info
4241 /// struct, used for member pointer types.
4242 void
4243 ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo(const MemberPointerType *Ty) {
4244  QualType PointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
4245 
4246  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
4247  // __flags is a flag word describing the cv-qualification and other
4248  // attributes of the type pointed to.
4249  unsigned Flags = extractPBaseFlags(CGM.getContext(), PointeeTy);
4250 
4251  const RecordType *ClassType = cast<RecordType>(Ty->getClass());
4252  if (IsIncompleteClassType(ClassType))
4253  Flags |= PTI_ContainingClassIncomplete;
4254 
4255  llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
4256  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
4257  Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
4258 
4259  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
4260  // __pointee is a pointer to the std::type_info derivation for the
4261  // unqualified type being pointed to.
4262  llvm::Constant *PointeeTypeInfo =
4263  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(PointeeTy);
4264  Fields.push_back(PointeeTypeInfo);
4265 
4266  // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p9:
4267  // __context is a pointer to an abi::__class_type_info corresponding to the
4268  // class type containing the member pointed to
4269  // (e.g., the "A" in "int A::*").
4270  Fields.push_back(
4271  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(QualType(ClassType, 0)));
4272 }

4274 llvm::Constant *ItaniumCXXABI::getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty) {
4275  return ItaniumRTTIBuilder(*this).BuildTypeInfo(Ty);
4276 }
