4278 void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitFundamentalRTTIDescriptors(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
4279  // Types added here must also be added to TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary.
4280  QualType FundamentalTypes[] = {
4281  getContext().VoidTy, getContext().NullPtrTy,
4282  getContext().BoolTy, getContext().WCharTy,
4283  getContext().CharTy, getContext().UnsignedCharTy,
4284  getContext().SignedCharTy, getContext().ShortTy,
4285  getContext().UnsignedShortTy, getContext().IntTy,
4286  getContext().UnsignedIntTy, getContext().LongTy,
4287  getContext().UnsignedLongTy, getContext().LongLongTy,
4288  getContext().UnsignedLongLongTy, getContext().Int128Ty,
4289  getContext().UnsignedInt128Ty, getContext().HalfTy,
4290  getContext().FloatTy, getContext().DoubleTy,
4291  getContext().LongDoubleTy, getContext().Float128Ty,
4292  getContext().Char8Ty, getContext().Char16Ty,
4293  getContext().Char32Ty
4294  };
4295  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes DLLStorageClass =
4296  RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() || CGM.shouldMapVisibilityToDLLExport(RD)
4297  ? llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass
4298  : llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass;
4299  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes Visibility =
4300  CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(RD->getVisibility());
4301  for (const QualType &FundamentalType : FundamentalTypes) {
4302  QualType PointerType = getContext().getPointerType(FundamentalType);
4303  QualType PointerTypeConst = getContext().getPointerType(
4304  FundamentalType.withConst());
4305  for (QualType Type : {FundamentalType, PointerType, PointerTypeConst})
4306  ItaniumRTTIBuilder(*this).BuildTypeInfo(
4307  Type, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
4308  Visibility, DLLStorageClass);
4309  }
4310 }
4311 
4312 /// What sort of uniqueness rules should we use for the RTTI for the
4313 /// given type?
4314 ItaniumCXXABI::RTTIUniquenessKind ItaniumCXXABI::classifyRTTIUniqueness(
4315  QualType CanTy, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage) const {
4316  if (shouldRTTIBeUnique())
4317  return RUK_Unique;
4318 
4319  // It's only necessary for linkonce_odr or weak_odr linkage.
4320  if (Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage &&
4321  Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage)
4322  return RUK_Unique;
4323 
4324  // It's only necessary with default visibility.
4325  if (CanTy->getVisibility() != DefaultVisibility)
4326  return RUK_Unique;
4327 
4328  // If we're not required to publish this symbol, hide it.
4329  if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage)
4330  return RUK_NonUniqueHidden;
4331 
4332  // If we're required to publish this symbol, as we might be under an
4333  // explicit instantiation, leave it with default visibility but
4334  // enable string-comparisons.
4335  assert(Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage);
4336  return RUK_NonUniqueVisible;
4337 }
4338 
4339 // Find out how to codegen the complete destructor and constructor
4340 namespace {
4341 enum class StructorCodegen { Emit, RAUW, Alias, COMDAT };
4342 }
4343 static StructorCodegen getCodegenToUse(CodeGenModule &CGM,
4344  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
4345  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CXXCtorDtorAliases)
4346  return StructorCodegen::Emit;
4347 
4348  // The complete and base structors are not equivalent if there are any virtual
4349  // bases, so emit separate functions.
4350  if (MD->getParent()->getNumVBases())
4351  return StructorCodegen::Emit;
4352 
4353  GlobalDecl AliasDecl;
4354  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD)) {
4355  AliasDecl = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Complete);
4356  } else {
4357  const auto *CD = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD);
4358  AliasDecl = GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete);
4359  }
4360  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getFunctionLinkage(AliasDecl);
4361 
4362  if (llvm::GlobalValue::isDiscardableIfUnused(Linkage))
4363  return StructorCodegen::RAUW;
4364 
4365  // FIXME: Should we allow available_externally aliases?
4366  if (!llvm::GlobalAlias::isValidLinkage(Linkage))
4367  return StructorCodegen::RAUW;
4368 
4369  if (llvm::GlobalValue::isWeakForLinker(Linkage)) {
4370  // Only ELF and wasm support COMDATs with arbitrary names (C5/D5).
4371  if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() ||
4372  CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatWasm())
4373  return StructorCodegen::COMDAT;
4374  return StructorCodegen::Emit;
4375  }
4376 
4377  return StructorCodegen::Alias;
4378 }
4379 
4380 static void emitConstructorDestructorAlias(CodeGenModule &CGM,
4381  GlobalDecl AliasDecl,
4382  GlobalDecl TargetDecl) {
4383  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getFunctionLinkage(AliasDecl);
4384 
4385  StringRef MangledName = CGM.getMangledName(AliasDecl);
4386  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = CGM.GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4387  if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration())
4388  return;
4389 
4390  auto *Aliasee = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CGM.GetAddrOfGlobal(TargetDecl));
4391 
4392  // Create the alias with no name.
4393  auto *Alias = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Linkage, "", Aliasee);
4394 
4395  // Constructors and destructors are always unnamed_addr.
4396  Alias->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
4397 
4398  // Switch any previous uses to the alias.
4399  if (Entry) {
4400  assert(Entry->getType() == Aliasee->getType() &&
4401  "declaration exists with different type");
4402  Alias->takeName(Entry);
4403  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(Alias);
4404  Entry->eraseFromParent();
4405  } else {
4406  Alias->setName(MangledName);
4407  }
4408 
4409  // Finally, set up the alias with its proper name and attributes.
4410  CGM.SetCommonAttributes(AliasDecl, Alias);
4411 }
4412 
4413 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitCXXStructor(GlobalDecl GD) {
4414  auto *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4415  auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD);
4416  const CXXDestructorDecl *DD = CD ? nullptr : cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD);
4417 
4418  StructorCodegen CGType = getCodegenToUse(CGM, MD);
4419 
4420  if (CD ? GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Complete
4421  : GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete) {
4422  GlobalDecl BaseDecl;
4423  if (CD)
4424  BaseDecl = GD.getWithCtorType(Ctor_Base);
4425  else
4426  BaseDecl = GD.getWithDtorType(Dtor_Base);
4427 
4428  if (CGType == StructorCodegen::Alias || CGType == StructorCodegen::COMDAT) {
4429  emitConstructorDestructorAlias(CGM, GD, BaseDecl);
4430  return;
4431  }
4432 
4433  if (CGType == StructorCodegen::RAUW) {
4434  StringRef MangledName = CGM.getMangledName(GD);
4435  auto *Aliasee = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobal(BaseDecl);
4436  CGM.addReplacement(MangledName, Aliasee);
4437  return;
4438  }
4439  }
4440 
4441  // The base destructor is equivalent to the base destructor of its
4442  // base class if there is exactly one non-virtual base class with a
4443  // non-trivial destructor, there are no fields with a non-trivial
4444  // destructor, and the body of the destructor is trivial.
4445  if (DD && GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base &&
4446  CGType != StructorCodegen::COMDAT &&
4447  !CGM.TryEmitBaseDestructorAsAlias(DD))
4448  return;
4449 
4450  // FIXME: The deleting destructor is equivalent to the selected operator
4451  // delete if:
4452  // * either the delete is a destroying operator delete or the destructor
4453  // would be trivial if it weren't virtual,
4454  // * the conversion from the 'this' parameter to the first parameter of the
4455  // destructor is equivalent to a bitcast,
4456  // * the destructor does not have an implicit "this" return, and
4457  // * the operator delete has the same calling convention and IR function type
4458  // as the destructor.
4459  // In such cases we should try to emit the deleting dtor as an alias to the
4460  // selected 'operator delete'.
4461 
4462  llvm::Function *Fn = CGM.codegenCXXStructor(GD);
4463 
4464  if (CGType == StructorCodegen::COMDAT) {
4465  SmallString<256> Buffer;
4466  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
4467  if (DD)
4468  getMangleContext().mangleCXXDtorComdat(DD, Out);
4469  else
4470  getMangleContext().mangleCXXCtorComdat(CD, Out);
4471  llvm::Comdat *C = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Out.str());
4472  Fn->setComdat(C);
4473  } else {
4474  CGM.maybeSetTrivialComdat(*MD, *Fn);
4475  }
4476 }
4477 
4478 static llvm::FunctionCallee getBeginCatchFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4479  // void *__cxa_begin_catch(void*);
4480  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4481  CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
4482 
4483  return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_begin_catch");
4484 }
4485 
4486 static llvm::FunctionCallee getEndCatchFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4487  // void __cxa_end_catch();
4488  llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
4489  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
4490 
4491  return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_end_catch");
4492 }
4493 
4494 static llvm::FunctionCallee getGetExceptionPtrFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4495  // void *__cxa_get_exception_ptr(void*);
4496  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4497  CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
4498 
4499  return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_get_exception_ptr");
4500 }
4501 
4502 namespace {
4503  /// A cleanup to call __cxa_end_catch. In many cases, the caught
4504  /// exception type lets us state definitively that the thrown exception
4505  /// type does not have a destructor. In particular:
4506  /// - Catch-alls tell us nothing, so we have to conservatively
4507  /// assume that the thrown exception might have a destructor.
4508  /// - Catches by reference behave according to their base types.
4509  /// - Catches of non-record types will only trigger for exceptions
4510  /// of non-record types, which never have destructors.
4511  /// - Catches of record types can trigger for arbitrary subclasses
4512  /// of the caught type, so we have to assume the actual thrown
4513  /// exception type might have a throwing destructor, even if the
4514  /// caught type's destructor is trivial or nothrow.
4515  struct CallEndCatch final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
4516  CallEndCatch(bool MightThrow) : MightThrow(MightThrow) {}
4517  bool MightThrow;
4518 
4519  void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
4520  if (!MightThrow) {
4521  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getEndCatchFn(CGF.CGM));
4522  return;
4523  }
4524 
4525  CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(getEndCatchFn(CGF.CGM));
4526  }
4527  };
4528 }
4529 
4530 /// Emits a call to __cxa_begin_catch and enters a cleanup to call
4531 /// __cxa_end_catch. If -fassume-nothrow-exception-dtor is specified, we assume
4532 /// that the exception object's dtor is nothrow, therefore the __cxa_end_catch
4533 /// call can be marked as nounwind even if EndMightThrow is true.
4534 ///
4535 /// \param EndMightThrow - true if __cxa_end_catch might throw
4536 static llvm::Value *CallBeginCatch(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4537  llvm::Value *Exn,
4538  bool EndMightThrow) {
4539  llvm::CallInst *call =
4540  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getBeginCatchFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4541 
4542  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallEndCatch>(
4543  NormalAndEHCleanup,
4544  EndMightThrow && !CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().AssumeNothrowExceptionDtor);
4545 
4546  return call;
4547 }
4548 
4549 /// A "special initializer" callback for initializing a catch
4550 /// parameter during catch initialization.
4551 static void InitCatchParam(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4552  const VarDecl &CatchParam,
4553  Address ParamAddr,
4554  SourceLocation Loc) {
4555  // Load the exception from where the landing pad saved it.
4556  llvm::Value *Exn = CGF.getExceptionFromSlot();
4557 
4558  CanQualType CatchType =
4559  CGF.CGM.getContext().getCanonicalType(CatchParam.getType());
4560  llvm::Type *LLVMCatchTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CatchType);
4561 
4562  // If we're catching by reference, we can just cast the object
4563  // pointer to the appropriate pointer.
4564  if (isa<ReferenceType>(CatchType)) {
4565  QualType CaughtType = cast<ReferenceType>(CatchType)->getPointeeType();
4566  bool EndCatchMightThrow = CaughtType->isRecordType();
4567 
4568  // __cxa_begin_catch returns the adjusted object pointer.
4569  llvm::Value *AdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, EndCatchMightThrow);
4570 
4571  // We have no way to tell the personality function that we're
4572  // catching by reference, so if we're catching a pointer,
4573  // __cxa_begin_catch will actually return that pointer by value.
4574  if (const PointerType *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(CaughtType)) {
4575  QualType PointeeType = PT->getPointeeType();
4576 
4577  // When catching by reference, generally we should just ignore
4578  // this by-value pointer and use the exception object instead.
4579  if (!PointeeType->isRecordType()) {
4580 
4581  // Exn points to the struct _Unwind_Exception header, which
4582  // we have to skip past in order to reach the exception data.
4583  unsigned HeaderSize =
4584  CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getSizeOfUnwindException();
4585  AdjustedExn =
4586  CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(CGF.Int8Ty, Exn, HeaderSize);
4587 
4588  // However, if we're catching a pointer-to-record type that won't
4589  // work, because the personality function might have adjusted
4590  // the pointer. There's actually no way for us to fully satisfy
4591  // the language/ABI contract here: we can't use Exn because it
4592  // might have the wrong adjustment, but we can't use the by-value
4593  // pointer because it's off by a level of abstraction.
4594  //
4595  // The current solution is to dump the adjusted pointer into an
4596  // alloca, which breaks language semantics (because changing the
4597  // pointer doesn't change the exception) but at least works.
4598  // The better solution would be to filter out non-exact matches
4599  // and rethrow them, but this is tricky because the rethrow
4600  // really needs to be catchable by other sites at this landing
4601  // pad. The best solution is to fix the personality function.
4602  } else {
4603  // Pull the pointer for the reference type off.
4604  llvm::Type *PtrTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CaughtType);
4605 
4606  // Create the temporary and write the adjusted pointer into it.
4607  Address ExnPtrTmp =
4608  CGF.CreateTempAlloca(PtrTy, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "exn.byref.tmp");
4609  llvm::Value *Casted = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, PtrTy);
4610  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Casted, ExnPtrTmp);
4611 
4612  // Bind the reference to the temporary.
4613  AdjustedExn = ExnPtrTmp.emitRawPointer(CGF);
4614  }
4615  }
4616 
4617  llvm::Value *ExnCast =
4618  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, LLVMCatchTy, "exn.byref");
4619  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(ExnCast, ParamAddr);
4620  return;
4621  }
4622 
4623  // Scalars and complexes.
4624  TypeEvaluationKind TEK = CGF.getEvaluationKind(CatchType);
4625  if (TEK != TEK_Aggregate) {
4626  llvm::Value *AdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, false);
4627 
4628  // If the catch type is a pointer type, __cxa_begin_catch returns
4629  // the pointer by value.
4630  if (CatchType->hasPointerRepresentation()) {
4631  llvm::Value *CastExn =
4632  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, LLVMCatchTy, "exn.casted");
4633 
4634  switch (CatchType.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime()) {
4635  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4636  CastExn = CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(CastExn);
4637  [[fallthrough]];
4638 
4639  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4640  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4641  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4642  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CastExn, ParamAddr);
4643  return;
4644 
4645  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4646  CGF.EmitARCInitWeak(ParamAddr, CastExn);
4647  return;
4648  }
4649  llvm_unreachable("bad ownership qualifier!");
4650  }
4651 
4652  // Otherwise, it returns a pointer into the exception object.
4653 
4654  LValue srcLV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(AdjustedExn, CatchType);
4655  LValue destLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ParamAddr, CatchType);
4656  switch (TEK) {
4657  case TEK_Complex:
4658  CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(CGF.EmitLoadOfComplex(srcLV, Loc), destLV,
4659  /*init*/ true);
4660  return;
4661  case TEK_Scalar: {
4662  llvm::Value *ExnLoad = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(srcLV, Loc);
4663  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(ExnLoad, destLV, /*init*/ true);
4664  return;
4665  }
4666  case TEK_Aggregate:
4667  llvm_unreachable("evaluation kind filtered out!");
4668  }
4669  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
4670  }
4671 
4672  assert(isa<RecordType>(CatchType) && "unexpected catch type!");
4673  auto catchRD = CatchType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4674  CharUnits caughtExnAlignment = CGF.CGM.getClassPointerAlignment(catchRD);
4675 
4676  llvm::Type *PtrTy =
4677  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext()); // addrspace 0 ok
4678 
4679  // Check for a copy expression. If we don't have a copy expression,
4680  // that means a trivial copy is okay.
4681  const Expr *copyExpr = CatchParam.getInit();
4682  if (!copyExpr) {
4683  llvm::Value *rawAdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4684  Address adjustedExn(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(rawAdjustedExn, PtrTy),
4685  LLVMCatchTy, caughtExnAlignment);
4686  LValue Dest = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ParamAddr, CatchType);
4687  LValue Src = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(adjustedExn, CatchType);
4688  CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dest, Src, CatchType, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
4689  return;
4690  }
4691 
4692  // We have to call __cxa_get_exception_ptr to get the adjusted
4693  // pointer before copying.
4694  llvm::CallInst *rawAdjustedExn =
4695  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGetExceptionPtrFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4696 
4697  // Cast that to the appropriate type.
4698  Address adjustedExn(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(rawAdjustedExn, PtrTy),
4699  LLVMCatchTy, caughtExnAlignment);
4700 
4701  // The copy expression is defined in terms of an OpaqueValueExpr.
4702  // Find it and map it to the adjusted expression.
4703  CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMapping
4704  opaque(CGF, OpaqueValueExpr::findInCopyConstruct(copyExpr),
4705  CGF.MakeAddrLValue(adjustedExn, CatchParam.getType()));
4706 
4707  // Call the copy ctor in a terminate scope.
4708  CGF.EHStack.pushTerminate();
4709 
4710  // Perform the copy construction.
4711  CGF.EmitAggExpr(copyExpr,
4712  AggValueSlot::forAddr(ParamAddr, Qualifiers(),
4713  AggValueSlot::IsNotDestructed,
4714  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
4715  AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
4716  AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
4717 
4718  // Leave the terminate scope.
4719  CGF.EHStack.popTerminate();
4720 
4721  // Undo the opaque value mapping.
4722  opaque.pop();
4723 
4724  // Finally we can call __cxa_begin_catch.
4725  CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4726 }
4727 
4728 /// Begins a catch statement by initializing the catch variable and
4729 /// calling __cxa_begin_catch.
4730 void ItaniumCXXABI::emitBeginCatch(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4731  const CXXCatchStmt *S) {
4732  // We have to be very careful with the ordering of cleanups here:
4733  // C++ [except.throw]p4:
4734  // The destruction [of the exception temporary] occurs
4735  // immediately after the destruction of the object declared in
4736  // the exception-declaration in the handler.
4737  //
4738  // So the precise ordering is:
4739  // 1. Construct catch variable.
4740  // 2. __cxa_begin_catch
4741  // 3. Enter __cxa_end_catch cleanup
4742  // 4. Enter dtor cleanup
4743  //
4744  // We do this by using a slightly abnormal initialization process.
4745  // Delegation sequence:
4746  // - ExitCXXTryStmt opens a RunCleanupsScope
4747  // - EmitAutoVarAlloca creates the variable and debug info
4748  // - InitCatchParam initializes the variable from the exception
4749  // - CallBeginCatch calls __cxa_begin_catch
4750  // - CallBeginCatch enters the __cxa_end_catch cleanup
4751  // - EmitAutoVarCleanups enters the variable destructor cleanup
4752  // - EmitCXXTryStmt emits the code for the catch body
4753  // - EmitCXXTryStmt close the RunCleanupsScope
4754 
4755  VarDecl *CatchParam = S->getExceptionDecl();
4756  if (!CatchParam) {
4757  llvm::Value *Exn = CGF.getExceptionFromSlot();
4758  CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4759  return;
4760  }
4761 
4762  // Emit the local.
4763  CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission var = CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(*CatchParam);
4764  InitCatchParam(CGF, *CatchParam, var.getObjectAddress(CGF), S->getBeginLoc());
4765  CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(var);
4766 }
4767 
4768 /// Get or define the following function:
4769 /// void @__clang_call_terminate(i8* %exn) nounwind noreturn
4770 /// This code is used only in C++.
4771 static llvm::FunctionCallee getClangCallTerminateFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4772  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
4773  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(
4774  C.VoidTy, {C.getPointerType(C.CharTy)});
4775  llvm::FunctionType *fnTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4776  llvm::FunctionCallee fnRef = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
4777  fnTy, "__clang_call_terminate", llvm::AttributeList(), /*Local=*/true);
4778  llvm::Function *fn =
4779  cast<llvm::Function>(fnRef.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts());
4780  if (fn->empty()) {
4781  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, fn, /*IsThunk=*/false);
4782  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, fn);
4783  fn->setDoesNotThrow();
4784  fn->setDoesNotReturn();
4785 
4786  // What we really want is to massively penalize inlining without
4787  // forbidding it completely. The difference between that and
4788  // 'noinline' is negligible.
4789  fn->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
4790 
4791  // Allow this function to be shared across translation units, but
4792  // we don't want it to turn into an exported symbol.
4793  fn->setLinkage(llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
4794  fn->setVisibility(llvm::Function::HiddenVisibility);
4795  if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
4796  fn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(fn->getName()));
4797 
4798  // Set up the function.
4799  llvm::BasicBlock *entry =
4800  llvm::BasicBlock::Create(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "", fn);
4801  CGBuilderTy builder(CGM, entry);
4802 
4803  // Pull the exception pointer out of the parameter list.
4804  llvm::Value *exn = &*fn->arg_begin();
4805 
4806  // Call __cxa_begin_catch(exn).
4807  llvm::CallInst *catchCall = builder.CreateCall(getBeginCatchFn(CGM), exn);
4808  catchCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4809  catchCall->setCallingConv(CGM.getRuntimeCC());
4810 
4811  // Call std::terminate().
4812  llvm::CallInst *termCall = builder.CreateCall(CGM.getTerminateFn());
4813  termCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4814  termCall->setDoesNotReturn();
4815  termCall->setCallingConv(CGM.getRuntimeCC());
4816 
4817  // std::terminate cannot return.
4818  builder.CreateUnreachable();
4819  }
4820  return fnRef;
4821 }

4823 llvm::CallInst *
4824 ItaniumCXXABI::emitTerminateForUnexpectedException(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4825  llvm::Value *Exn) {
4826  // In C++, we want to call __cxa_begin_catch() before terminating.
4827  if (Exn) {
4828  assert(CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
4829  return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getClangCallTerminateFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4830  }
4831  return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGF.CGM.getTerminateFn());
4832 }

4848 llvm::CallInst *
4849 WebAssemblyCXXABI::emitTerminateForUnexpectedException(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4850  llvm::Value *Exn) {
4851  // Itanium ABI calls __clang_call_terminate(), which __cxa_begin_catch() on
4852  // the violating exception to mark it handled, but it is currently hard to do
4853  // with wasm EH instruction structure with catch/catch_all, we just call
4854  // std::terminate and ignore the violating exception as in CGCXXABI.

4860 /// Register a global destructor as best as we know how.
4861 void XLCXXABI::registerGlobalDtor(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl &D,
4862  llvm::FunctionCallee Dtor,
4863  llvm::Constant *Addr) {
4864  if (D.getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None) {
4865  llvm::PointerType *PtrTy =
4866  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CGF.getLLVMContext());
4867 
4868  // extern "C" int __pt_atexit_np(int flags, int(*)(int,...), ...);
4869  llvm::FunctionType *AtExitTy =
4870  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.IntTy, {CGM.IntTy, PtrTy}, true);
4871 
4872  // Fetch the actual function.
4873  llvm::FunctionCallee AtExit =
4874  CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(AtExitTy, "__pt_atexit_np");
4875 
4876  // Create __dtor function for the var decl.
4877  llvm::Function *DtorStub = CGF.createTLSAtExitStub(D, Dtor, Addr, AtExit);
4878 
4879  // Register above __dtor with atexit().
4880  // First param is flags and must be 0, second param is function ptr
4881  llvm::Value *NV = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.IntTy);
4882  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(AtExit, {NV, DtorStub});
4883 
4884  // Cannot unregister TLS __dtor so done
4885  return;
4886  }
4887 
4888  // Create __dtor function for the var decl.
4889  llvm::Function *DtorStub = CGF.createAtExitStub(D, Dtor, Addr);
4890 
4891  // Register above __dtor with atexit().
4892  CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithAtExit(DtorStub);
4893 
4894  // Emit __finalize function to unregister __dtor and (as appropriate) call
4895  // __dtor.
4896  emitCXXStermFinalizer(D, DtorStub, Addr);
4897 }
4898 
4899 void XLCXXABI::emitCXXStermFinalizer(const VarDecl &D, llvm::Function *dtorStub,
4900  llvm::Constant *addr) {
4901  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, false);
4902  SmallString<256> FnName;
4903  {
4904  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(FnName);
4905  getMangleContext().mangleDynamicStermFinalizer(&D, Out);
4906  }
4907 
4908  // Create the finalization action associated with a variable.
4909  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
4910  llvm::Function *StermFinalizer = CGM.CreateGlobalInitOrCleanUpFunction(
4911  FTy, FnName.str(), FI, D.getLocation());
4912 
4913  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
4914 
4915  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), CGM.getContext().VoidTy, StermFinalizer, FI,
4916  FunctionArgList(), D.getLocation(),
4917  D.getInit()->getExprLoc());
4918 
4919  // The unatexit subroutine unregisters __dtor functions that were previously
4920  // registered by the atexit subroutine. If the referenced function is found,
4921  // the unatexit returns a value of 0, meaning that the cleanup is still
4922  // pending (and we should call the __dtor function).
4923  llvm::Value *V = CGF.unregisterGlobalDtorWithUnAtExit(dtorStub);
4924 
4925  llvm::Value *NeedsDestruct = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(V, "needs_destruct");
4926 
4927  llvm::BasicBlock *DestructCallBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("destruct.call");
4928  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("destruct.end");
4929 
4930  // Check if unatexit returns a value of 0. If it does, jump to
4931  // DestructCallBlock, otherwise jump to EndBlock directly.
4932  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(NeedsDestruct, DestructCallBlock, EndBlock);
4933 
4934  CGF.EmitBlock(DestructCallBlock);
4935 
4936  // Emit the call to dtorStub.
4937  llvm::CallInst *CI = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(dtorStub);
4938 
4939  // Make sure the call and the callee agree on calling convention.
4940  CI->setCallingConv(dtorStub->getCallingConv());
4941 
4942  CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
4943 
4944  CGF.FinishFunction();
4945 
4946  if (auto *IPA = D.getAttr<InitPriorityAttr>()) {
4947  CGM.AddCXXPrioritizedStermFinalizerEntry(StermFinalizer,
4948  IPA->getPriority());
4949  } else if (isTemplateInstantiation(D.getTemplateSpecializationKind()) ||
4950  getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(&D) == GVA_DiscardableODR) {
4951  // According to C++ [basic.start.init]p2, class template static data
4952  // members (i.e., implicitly or explicitly instantiated specializations)
4953  // have unordered initialization. As a consequence, we can put them into
4954  // their own llvm.global_dtors entry.
4955  CGM.AddCXXStermFinalizerToGlobalDtor(StermFinalizer, 65535);
4956  } else {
4957  CGM.AddCXXStermFinalizerEntry(StermFinalizer);
4958  }
4959 }
V
#define V(N, I)
